title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift all together in a bowl #1.

title: hole-punched cake
directions: Mix cake mix and ingredients called for on package as directed and bake in oblong pan.
Punch holes in cake.
Heat 2 c. milk, 2 c. sugar long enough to dissolve sugar.
Pour over cake and into holes.
Spread cool whip on top, then sprinkle with frozen coconut.

title: glorified rice
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add rice.
Do not stir.
Cover.
Turn down heat to simmer and cook rice until tender and water is absorbed, about 17 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, add oil then carrots.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add flour, then well beaten eggs, buttermilk and coconut.
Pour into uncooked pastry shell. Cook at 350° until golden.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda.
In a separate bowl, cream brown sugar, sugar and butter, then stir in vanilla and eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Add in chocolate chips.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: eight can soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Put in bottom of crock-pot. Mix all 8 cans together and put in crock-pot. Cook all day. The leftovers can be frozen for later.

title: unsinkable sauerkraut
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine with undrained sauerkraut and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In large pot, melt the oleo; stir in the flour.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add potatoes and onions.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn cheese pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Good!

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Add eggs to cake mix.
Add cherry pie filling.
(Do not use a mixer, use a slotted spoon.)
Add extract.
Bake 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar together.
Add flour and nuts to make crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Blend 1/4 cup white sugar and cream cheese in bowl until smooth.
Add eggs, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 16 pieces.
Can be frozen.

title: cherry or blueberry squares
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, then slowly add flour.
Batter will be thick.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Spoon and spread with fork rest of batter over filling.
If not all filling is covered, it will bake over.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Serves 30 squares.

title: vanilla cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Dough will be fairly stiff. You can also add nuts, coconut or chocolate chips to this recipe. Use approximately 1 cup.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool before taking up.

title: jeff davis jelly roll
directions: Rub butter and sugar together.
Add the beaten yolks, the milk, then whip whites and flour lightly and quickly.
Bake in a large buttered pan.
Turn out on a clean, damp cloth.
Spread with jelly and roll up closely.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk and margarine; pour over bread crumbs and sugar. Stir well until bread becomes very soft.
Beat eggs; mix well with bread mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Refrigerate.
Very good hot or cold.

title: no fail pie meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water in a small saucepan over medium heat until thick and clear, stirring constantly (about 1 minute).
Cool.
Beat whites until frothy.
Add a small pinch of salt and continue beating until peaks hold shape.
Fold the cooled, thickening mixture into the egg whites.
Spread over a cooled cream pie, sealing to the edges.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all together except water.
Add water as you need it to make it all blend.
Roll paper thin on a floured board, keeping the shape rectangular as much as possible.
Allow to stand 20 minutes.
Roll up and slice 1/8-inch wide for fine noodles or 1/2 inch for broad ones.
Toss lightly to separate strand and spread out to dry for several hours.
Cook on low heat for about 45 minutes to one hour.
For good taste use chicken or beef cubes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 baking dish.
Place 1 to 1 1/2 slices of cheese per chicken breast.
Combine soup with milk and pour over chicken.
Melt butter and combine with bread crumbs and pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Prepare rice as indicated on package.
Serve chicken over rice.

title: dream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and blend.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a shallow dish.
Mix sour cream with seasonings and pour over chicken.
Turn each piece until it is well coated.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, roll each breast in bread crumbs and return to refrigerator to chill at least 1 1/2 hours.
Place a dab of butter on each roll.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cover pan for first half of baking time.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Add the dressing mix to the mashed potatoes. Stir well and add butter or margarine as desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinade
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly; add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add mashed bananas and flavoring; fold in dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-cranberry relish
directions: Combine sugar, water and orange rind in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer until clear (about 2 minutes).
Add apple and cook 5 minutes.
Add cranberries and spices.
Simmer 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir in raisins.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tabbouli
directions: Wash burghul under water and press down on burghul as you pour out water to squeeze out excess water.
Add tomatoes.
Set aside for a couple of minutes.
Separately mix yellow onions, salt and pepper.
Crush this together with hand until juicy; add to tomatoes and burghul.
Add parsley, green onion and mint.
Mix together.
Add olive oil and lemon juice and mix again.
Pour into serving dish.
Decorate with diced tomatoes.

title: four layer sin
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and 3/4 cup nuts; press into an oblong baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: green bean salad
directions: Trim beans and cut into pieces, about 1 1/2-inches.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Drain and cool to lukewarm.
Add onion, garlic, parsley, olive oil and salt and pepper and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: savory vegetable platter
directions: Heat bouillon, savory and tarragon to a boil.
Add cauliflower; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Make a sauce of butter, seed and juice. Serve vegetables in clusters on a large platter.
Drizzle sauce over all.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large punch bowl.
Stir real well and serve.

title: green punch
directions: Mix liquids in punch bowl, then scoop sherbet into liquids.

title: mushroom turnovers
directions: Knead the cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup butter until smooth. Shape into ball and refrigerate 1 hour until chilled.
Saute 3 tablespoons butter and cook until mushrooms and onion are tender.
Turn heat off and mix in sour cream and 2 tablespoons flour.
Roll half of the dough 1/8-inch thick. Cut with round cutter (2 3/4-inch) about 20 circles.
Place mixture on half of the circle. Brush edges with egg and fold dough over. Press edges with fork. Prick tops and brush with egg. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: see's fudge
directions: Mix egg and sugar together. Melt chocolate chips and butter in oven and blend into eggs and sugar. Add chopped nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal coconut cake(microwave)
directions: Combine oats and water in a glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High uncovered for 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring once.
Set aside.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix all yolks and ingredients together and put back into whites created when you removed the yolks from the whites.

title: communion bread
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Mix in butter and shortening.
Add water gradually to make a stiff dough.
Divide into 2 pieces.
Roll out to 1/4-inch in greased pan.
Mark with straight edge knife into 1/2-inch squares.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.
Serves 200 people.

title: best punch in town
directions: Mix water, citric acid and sugar. Color with food coloring. Freeze in small containers.
When ready to serve, put frozen mixture in punch bowl and add juice and lemon-lime soda.
Makes a slushy punch.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Put milk (3 cups), sugar and margarine in microwave bowl; cook (heat) 10 minutes.
While heating, beat cornstarch, 2 eggs, 3/4 cup milk and vanilla, then slowly pour in the heated milk and cook 6 minutes or a little longer.
I beat with hand mixer after cooking, then pour into pie shell.
Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle 3/4 crumbs in bottom of pie crust. Pour in filling and put rest of crumbs on top.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; add chicken and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade and reserve marinade.
Heat oil and stir-fry chicken for 2 to 3 minutes or until it is no longer pink.
With a slotted spoon, remove chicken and set aside.
In the same skillet, stir-fry broccoli and carrots for 3 minutes or just until crisp-tender.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, hoisin sauce, ginger and reserved marinade.
Stir into vegetables.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and heated through.
Stir in cashews and chicken; heat through.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together chicken soup, chicken, 3/4 pint sour cream, green chilies, salt and onion.
Soften tortillas in hot cooking oil for just a few seconds; drain on paper towel.
Put a portion of the filling in the middle of each tortilla with a small amount of the grated cheese on each.
Roll.
Place in a long baking dish that has been lined with small amount of filling.
After all enchiladas are assembled, add remaining sauce on top, then add rest of sour cream and any grated cheese remaining.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: layered pudding cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Add 1/3 large container of Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Add milk to pudding.
Beat until thick.
Spread over creamy mixture.
Cover pudding layer with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Beat well. Pour in crust.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Let cool for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate covered candy
directions: Melt in top of double boiler.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Put a cupcake liner in cupcake pan; place a wafer in each liner (for crust).
Mix well next 3 ingredients.
Fill each liner 1/2 full with mixture; sprinkle on a little colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Cut steak into 1/4-inch strips and charbroil until rare.
In medium bowl, mix lime juice, soy sauce, Tabasco and black pepper. Add beef strips and coat them well.
Cover, refrigerate and marinate them for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn them occasionally.
Remove the beef strips from the marinade.

title: cheesy onion casserole
directions: Place onions in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan. Blend in flour.
Slowly stir in milk; cook until thick.
Keep flame low.
Stir in seasonings and cheese.
Pour over onions. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parslied rice
directions: In 1-quart casserole, stir water and parsley together.
Cook in microwave, with cover, on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture is boiling.
Stir in rice.
Let stand, with cover, 5 minutes.

title: jackstraw eggplant
directions: Halve eggplant lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices. Cut slices in 1/2-inch strips.
Beat together flour, ice water, egg, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Dip strips into mixture.
Fry a few at a time in enough oil to cover at 365° for 4 to 5 minutes, turning.
Drain on paper toweling.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop up chipped beef.
Finely chop the small onion.
Mix together with the cream cheese and garlic salt.
Roll into ball. Refrigerate.

title: herbed roquefort biscuits
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a medium bowl.
Cut in cheese mixture and butter with a pastry blender. Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead lightly 7 to 8 times. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Yields 14 biscuits.

title: boston cookies
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco, eggs, salt, vanilla and cinnamon.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Put one extra cup of flour on dates and pecans.
Add dates, pecans and flour last.
Drop on cookie sheet (not too close) and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pizza twists
directions: Separate and unroll breadsticks.
Place 3 or more slices of pepperoni in a single layer over 1/2 of each breadstick.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons sauce over the pepperoni.
Sprinkle a little cheese over the sauce.
Fold remaining half of breadstick over the top, sealing the ends.
Twist the breadstick into a figure eight. Mix 2 tablespoons cheese with Italian seasoning and garlic powder. Sprinkle over each stick.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with heated pizza sauce.
For a crunchy crust, lightly sprinkle bottoms with cornmeal.
Makes 8.
Very good for school lunches.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well.
Add oil, water and eggs. Blend.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Makes 3 4 1/2 by 8 1/2 inch pans.
Grease or spray tins.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: biscuits
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, cream of tartar and salt.
Cut in shortening, margarine or butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center; add milk all at once.
Stir just until dough clings together.

title: quick vegetable soup(microwave)
directions: Place bacon in single layer in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until crisp; set aside.
Preserve 1 tablespoon of drippings; discard remainder.
Add vegetables, tomatoes, cut into small pieces, onion, bouillon and garlic powder to drippings. Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High 9 to 11 minutes or until steaming hot and flavors are blended.
Crumble bacon and add to soup.
Sprinkle cheese over individual bowls of soup.
Makes about 4 servings (125 calories).

title: mexican wedding ring cookies
directions: Work together all ingredients like biscuits. Roll into small 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef in blender several slices at a time.
Soften cream cheese (microwave 20 to 30 seconds).
Add onion, 1/2 chopped beef, Worcestershire sauce and Accent; mix well.
Roll cheese ball in remaining beef.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter mix
directions: Boil sugar and light Karo for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Boil another 1 minute.
Add cereal and peanuts to the boiled mixture.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Break apart.
Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill pie shell with berries, then prepare glaze.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
In pan, cook green pepper with garlic salt in oil until tender.
Blend in soup and 1/3 to 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Add chicken, pineapple and soy sauce.
Heat and stir now and then over low heat.
Serve over rice.

title: diabetic bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and salt in water in large bowl.
Add soybean flour, stirring slowly; add the gluten flour and mix well into a soft dough.
Cover with a clean cloth, let rise until almost doubled in bulk, then punch dough down, and let rise 30 minutes more.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board; cut into loaf sizes (2 pieces). Shape into loaves, place into greased loaf pans.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Then bake in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes.

title: chandra's broccoli and beef
directions: Heat skillet.
Brown rice in oil.
Add other ingredients and bring to boil.
Simmer covered 15 to 20 minutes.

title: whole wheat molasses quick bread
directions: Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
In large bowl with fork mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, with fork, mix buttermilk, molasses and salad oil.
Stir in flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into pans. Bake 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread in pans on wire rack ten minutes.
Then remove from pans.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and sprinkle over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: ground beef vegetable soup(makes 14 cups)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion until meat is slightly brown in large saucepot; drain fat.
Add uncooked vegetables, tomatoes, seasonings, bouillon and 5 cups of water.
Simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add undrained canned vegetables. Heat for 5 minutes.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms in the microwave
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms.
Remove stems; chop fine.
Put caps on paper towel on micro-safe plate.
Microwave on High (70%) for 1 minute.
Drain and set aside.
Place butter, stems and onion in small bowl; microwave on High, 100%, until onion and stems are tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Then add the rest of your ingredients except cheese.
Mix until smooth, then microwave on High, 70%, until thickened, another 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir once or twice.
Then add cheese.
Fill caps.
Use 9-inch pie plate and microwave on High, 100%, another 1 to 2 minutes.
Sprinkle any filling leftover on top.
Serve; enjoy.

title: never fail refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup of milk with shortening and sugar.
Heat until blended.
Do not boil.
Add remaining milk.
Cool to lukewarm (110°).
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and add to milk mixture.
Stir together flour, sal, soda and baking powder.
Add to milk mixture.
Mix to form a dough.
Roll and cut amount needed.
Refrigerate remaining dough in covered container.
Will keep 7 to 10 days.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in medium size iron skillet.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over hot melted margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: perfect party mix
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Store in covered container and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for a couple of months.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy. Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Sift flour, then measure 3 cups flour (sifted with soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon). Add to first mixture and blend. Stir in nuts. Bake in 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour. (Line bottom of pans with greased waxed paper.) Remove from pans at once and cool on rack.

title: no bake white chocolate cookies
directions: Pour melted chocolate over all ingredients; stir well. Drop on waxed paper by spoon size desired.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Separate into flakes.
Put oil in a skillet.
Add bread, onion, salt and pepper.
Brown it lightly.
Put salmon liquor into a cup and pour in enough milk to equal 1 cup.
Combine salmon, crumbs and liquor. Add parsley and egg; blend, being careful not to mash salmon.
Pour into a greased 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Blend thoroughly and press into bottom of a 13
x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: rouladen (german beef rolls)
directions: Spread steaks with mustard.
Place slice of bacon length of steak, then pickle slice across this, towards top of steak.
Roll. Enter toothpick through steak roll, making sure end is secure. Brown in deep fry pan.
Remove, add water and bouillon, stir. Return steak rolls to pan, reduce heat and simmer in covered pan for 1 hour.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg, add the molasses and sifted dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls, dip into sugar. Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: buttermilk pies
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix together.
Add eggs and buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
Melt margarine and add to mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Pour in unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife comes out clean when inserted in the center of the pie.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Stir in taco seasoning and let cool.
In a large bowl, toss lettuce, tomato, radishes, green onion, beans and cheese.
Just before serving, toss with meat, corn chips and just enough dressing to coat lightly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately.
Saute onion and celery. Mix vegetables and add soups, then cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into freezer until firm.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together; press into jelly roll pan.
Melt chocolate chips and the peanut butter.
Spread over bottom layer.
Refrigerate. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: scallops a la newburg
directions: Saute scallops in butter.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and simmer 1 minute.
Set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and make roux with 1 tablespoon flour.
Slowly stir in 3/4 cup half and half.
Return scallops and simmer 2 minutes.
Add 1 egg yolk and 2 tablespoons sherry.
Serve with rice.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Halve pepper lengthwise; remove stems, seeds and membranes. Add 2 teaspoons salt and enough water to cover peppers and boil 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Take 1 pound of hot dogs and dip each one in the batter with a fork. Fry in a wire basket deep fryer until golden brown, about 3 minutes at 375°.
Drain on paper.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown beef, drain and pour into saucepan.
Stir in 1/2 c. sauce and 1 c. cheese.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.
Spread 1/2 c. sauce in 9 inch x 13 inch baking dish.
Spoon about 2 Tbsp. meat mixture down center of tortilla.
Roll up and place seam-side down in baking dish. Repeat with remaining tortillas.
Top with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 10 - 12 enchiladas.

title: baked dried fruit
directions: Place apricots and prunes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add orange sections and pineapple.
Top with pie filling.
Pour sherry over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: my favorite fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: helen's pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add sour cream and eggs.
Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: linda's luscious lemon pie
directions: In skillet, combine cornstarch, salt and sugar. Stir in water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Remove from heat.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook frozen broccoli. Drain and chop. Set aside. Mix rest of ingredients with beater. Stir in broccoli and 1 cup of shredded cheese. Pour into greased casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: country club rolls
directions: Combine and dissolve Crisco and boiling water.
Then add cold water and salt.
Beat together sugar and eggs.
Add to first mixture.
Then add yeast which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add gradually to mixture the flour.
Mix well. Put in greased bowl and cover.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Roll out on floured board.
Cut with small cutter.
Dip in melted butter.
Fold as pocketbook roll.
Cover biscuit pan with dish cloth.
Let rise until double bulk.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Put rolls close together in pan.
They can be baked and then frozen. Put in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
They are like you just baked them.
This is good and will stay good for several days, even if you don't freeze.

title: fruit punch
directions: Cook sugar in 3 cups water until dissolved; cool.
In large container, add juices and mix.
Add water according to each can. Add bananas.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Can freeze.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Put dry ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over it, then make 2 holes. In first hole, pour vinegar, in second hole pour vanilla and then add water.
Stir with fork until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: In a separate bowl, mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add apples and walnut pieces a little at a time.
Add dry ingredients to wet.

title: onion-bell pepper roasted potatoes
directions: Cut each potato crosswise about each 1/4-inch almost through; fan open.
Alternate slices of onion and bell pepper in potato. Salt and pepper. Brush with melted margarine.
Loosely wrap each stuffed potato in foil.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Let stand another 10 minutes.
Serves 8; contains about 160 calories each.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and vinegar. Mix well. Add slightly beaten eggs, coconut and pecans. Stir well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Do not cut until pie is cold.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut, celery, bell pepper, onion and pimentos in large bowl.
In saucepan, combine sugar, apple juice, apple cider vinegar and oil.
Bring to boil and pour over vegetables.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Blend ingredients together and refrigerate or you may freeze for later.

title: beef and bean burritos
directions: Brown beef with onion, bell pepper and seasonings.
Drain. Add refried beans (might need water added).
Simmer.
Prepare Ro-Tel dip as directed.
Set aside.
Spoon meat in tortillas. Fold tortillas and place in baking dish.
Pour Ro-Tel over tortillas and place in oven on low temperature to heat through.

title: crabmeat lasagna
directions: Assemble as you would any lasagna; top with sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: brownie-oat cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: goopy cake
directions: Measure into mixing bowl margarine, sugar, 2/3 cup of milk and flour.
Mix on low speed for 2 minutes, then stir in baking powder. Now add eggs, 1/3 cup milk and vanilla.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch cake pan in preheated oven (375°) for 20 minutes, or until center of cake springs back when touched.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Sort cucumbers according to size in jars.
Place 1 sprig of dill and a small hot pepper in jars.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Seal jars.
Wait 2 1/2 weeks before eating.

title: easy escalloped chicken
directions: Boil chicken in 2 quarts water until tender.
Remove bones and cut in medium pieces.
Reserve broth.
Combine in large mixing bowl: toasted bread, hard-boiled eggs, salt and pepper; set aside.

title: applesauce mold
directions: Boil 2 cups water and 1/2 cup red hots until dissolved.
Add cherry jello.
Mix and add applesauce.
Pour into mold.
When set and you are ready to serve, unmold onto a plate and fill hole with cottage cheese.

title: vegetarian pate
directions: Combine ingredients in blender until smooth.
Put in dish of your choice.
Refrigerate and serve on whole wheat crackers.

title: french puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place paper liner in each of 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In medium bowl, beat egg.
Stir milk and oil into egg mixture. Make a well in the flour mixture; pour egg into it.
Stir together with fork only until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fill muffin 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes, or until golden brown. Immediately roll hot muffins in 1/2 cup margarine or butter, melted, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cool on cooling rack.

title: crawfish cheese dip or sauce
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper until almost done.
Add garlic and cook.
Add crawfish and liquid from package.
Cook until crawfish curl and vegetables no longer crunch.
Add Velveeta cubes and melt over low temperature.
Dilute 1 Tablespoon cornstarch and add to dip.
Sauce will thicken the more it cooks.
Add salsa and Tony's Creole seasoning for a little more zing!

title: hot salsa
directions: Boil 1 hour, put in jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, 1 clove chopped garlic, salt and pepper.
Fold out onto large piece of wax paper and pat out into large rectangle, approximately 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cover with applesauce, onion, carrot, cheese and remaining garlic.
Roll, starting at side, until all is rolled.
Pinch ends together to seal.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: easy pie shell
directions: Combine ingredients and press into pan.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients (for the crust) in a 9-inch pie pan and shape by hand.
Bake at 450° about 5 minutes or until lightly brown.
Mix next five ingredients (for the filling) together, and boil until thick and clear.
Add 2 to 3 drops red food coloring and 2 tablespoons strawberry Jell-O.
Allow filling to cool; then mix with strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until serving time.
This is best served the same day.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour, alternating with sour cream, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch tube pan, lined on bottom with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Turn out and cool.

title: pizza styled steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces and brown in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add all ingredients to pan and cook covered for 1 hour and 15 minutes, then cook uncovered for 15 minutes more.
Always stir occasionally.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grate cranberries.
Mix with 1/2 cup sugar and set overnight. Combine grapes with pecans.
Add to cranberries.
Whip cream with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Fold in whipped cream and add marshmallows.

title: poppy seed roll
directions: Roll out on counter the hot roll mix to a thin layer. Spread butter all over rolled out mix. Spread poppy seed mixture on top of butter. Sprinkle lightly with sugar. Roll up tightly and place on cookie sheet in circle or in an angel food cake pan. Pinch to seal edges. Spread butter on top to brown. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: red beans and sausage
directions: Cook beans and spices slowly until beans are done. Add sausage when beans are cooked.
Let beans and sausage come to a boil, then let simmer. Serve over rice.

title: quick chili-rice dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add spices, corn, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Brown meat; pour off excess grease.
Add onions, garlic, tomato paste and seasonings to meat.
Let simmer about 15 minutes to develop flavor.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from water to cool.
Cook noodles in water.
In large saucepan, saute peppers in margarine.
Stir in 5 tablespoons flour, 1 at a time.
Add in milk to form a paste (consistency of Elmer's glue).
Add in cheese (grated) until melted, then add in soups, mushrooms and pimentos.
Add in cooked noodles, chicken, soy sauce and garlic salt to taste.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add egg and milk.
Stir and put in pan.
Add cherries but do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar if using fresh or frozen fruit.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Add sugar to peeled and chopped apples.
Let stand 10 minutes. Stir in melted margarine and beaten egg.
Blend.
Add to apple mixture flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch pan (greased) at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve plain or sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat together.
Bake according to box directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter cup bars
directions: Mix together the melted butter, powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over warm water.
Spread over crust.
Cool in refrigerator 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt butter; pour over bread crumbs.
Fold in raisins.
Turn into a greased baking dish.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir into hot scalded milk.
Pour over bread and let stand 15 minutes.
Set dish in a pan of water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with white sauce.

title: mom's pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 375° to 400°.
Beat 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Stir in Cool Whip and spread on pretzel mixture.
Combine strawberry jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries and let stand 10 minutes, until thickened.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Put the egg white, sugar and water in the top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat with a rotary eggbeater for seven minutes.
Then add baking powder and flavoring.
Remove from heat, beat until thick and spread in swirls over cake.

title: shrimp (or turkey) creole
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp or turkey; bring to boil. Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp or turkey; heat thoroughly. Serve over hot rice.
Good way to use leftover turkey!

title: daddy's catfish stew(serves 50)
directions: Boil fish until tender.
Remove from water, cool, and de-bone.
Dice or grate potatoes and cook in the fish water until thoroughly done.
Fry bacon and brown onions in grease.
Remove onions and add grease to potatoes and water.
Add de-boned fish and cook slowly about 1/2 hour.
Stirring occasionally.
Heat milk and add to fish mixture.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Do not let boil!
Add boiled eggs diced finely before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cover 2 cookie sheets with foil which has been coated with butter.
Place first 4 ingredients in electric skillet at 400°; cook until brown (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Stir constantly. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Very quickly pour into pans.
Spread ingredients while pouring.
Let cool 30 minutes; break.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add the next 9 ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: butter crust
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix just until dough forms. Press into
pan.
Bake
for
to
15 minutes, until golden. Cool. Fill with desired filling.

title: salmon ball appetizers
directions: Blend all ingredients till smooth.
Mold mixture into a small bowl lined with plastic wrap.
Remove from mold, garnish with parsley.
Can be designed in the shape of a fish.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Serve with crackers, toast rounds, rye bread, etc.

title: dean heaton's hominy casserole
directions: Combine hominy, chilies, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Mix well.
Spoon in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and extra cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.
Garnish if desired.
Serve hot.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant and drain.
Add all ingredients except half of cheese.
Mix and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese on top and return to oven until melts.

title: old-fashioned nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt together in mixing bowl.
Add the egg and milk to dry ingredients and mix together. Stir in walnuts. Pour into three greased 12 x 4-inch bread pans. Let raise for 20 minutes.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat vidalia onion casserole
directions: In medium saucepan combine onions with water to cover.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Drain well.
Transfer to 8-inch square baking dish, sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and juice from pineapple. Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy; fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, whipping cream and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: coca-cola pork chops
directions: Mix ketchup and Coke well and pour over pork chops.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pork chops luau
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork chops, and mix well. Marinate pork chops in sauce in a flat baking dish several hours, turning once or twice.
Place chops on grill 6 inches from coals; sear on both sides.
Cook slowly, basting frequently with sauce, 40 minutes or until done.
May be served with pineapple slices, peach halves or applesauce.
(Sometimes I marinate in refrigerator all day or overnight, turning when I can.)

title: squash casserole
directions: While squash are cooking, in blender or food processor, add soup to onion chunks and carrot chunks until blended.
Add this mixture to the cooked and drained squash along with butter, sour cream and stuffing.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash
baked potatoes with oleo.
Add all other ingredients. Mix
well.
Pour into 3 pie shells and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Use a 2-quart bean pot.
Soak beans overnight in water with 1 teaspoon baking soda.
In the morning, rinse beans well.
Cover beans with fresh water and parboil them for 10 minutes, then drain.
Dice rind of salt pork in 1/2-inch cubes.
If using ham bone, put in bean pot instead of salt pork.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Add beans and enough water to cover beans.
Bake in a 300° oven for 6 hours or at 350° for 4 hours or until beans are done.
Add small amount of water if beans are drying out.
Keep beans moist.

title: chesapeake oyster loaf
directions: Cut off top crust of bread and scoop out inside.
Butter 1/3 of bits of bread scooped out and toast in oven.
Fry oysters in butter; add cream, celery, pepper, salt, Tabasco and Old Bay and toasted bread.
Fill the hollowed loaf with this mixture; cover with top crust and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes, basting often with oyster liquor.
Slice and serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peachy poppy seed muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Combine the flour, poppy seeds, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with the baby food. Fill paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until muffins test done. Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken casserole(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Place rice in casserole first, then chicken, soups and water. Cook in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Cover the dish while cooking.

title: steamed carrot pudding
directions: Thoroughly oil a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Sift flour with soda, sugar, salt and spices.
Gradually stir butter into eggs in large bowl.
Then stir in flour mixture and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into prepared mold.

title: biloxi butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with assorted crackers. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Shred chicken and put on top of broccoli.
Mix together mayonnaise, soup, cheese and lemon juice in a bowl.
Put this mixture on top of chicken.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then in crumb mixture. Place in single layer on foil-lined sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for about 10 minutes or longer, depending on size of chicken pieces (until golden brown).

title: 8 minute cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: pimiento cheese sandwiches
directions: Boil seeds in boiling water for 2 hours with 1 teaspoon salt. Drain and put in a 250° oven for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: wedding chicken
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Lay cut up chicken on bottom. Spread chicken with Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and milk; layer over cheese.
Pour stuffing mix over soup.
Melt butter and drizzle over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil during last 20 minutes.

title: san francisco chicken
directions: Cut the chicken breasts in half.
In one dish, mix the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and parsley.
In another dish, melt the butter, plus 1 clove garlic (minced).
Take chicken pieces and white pepper both sides.
Put in butter and garlic. Roll in bread crumb mixture.
Roll up and toothpick together.
Put all rolled chicken in casserole dish.
Pour remaining butter
and garlic in casserole.
Squirt lemon juice over all chicken. Sprinkle paprika over it.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tayler's daddy's favorite spaghetti squash!
directions: Cut spaghetti squash in half.
Place face down in glass Pyrex in 2 inches of water.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
In separate pan, brown and season to taste ground turkey; add garlic, onion, all the peppers and mushrooms.
Let all ingredients cook together 10 to 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Season to taste.
When spaghetti squash is done, turn squash right side up and fork out spaghetti looking squash.
Serve the ingredients over squash.
Very tasty!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken breasts in chicken broth seasoned with black pepper and garlic powder. You may need to add a little water to this, but try to add as little as possible, because you want the sauce to be creamy, not diluted.

title: baked pinto beans
directions: Cook beans until almost done.
Brown bacon or ham in skillet, then add other ingredients.
Add all ingredients to beans and finish cooking in the oven.

title: mushroom-stuffed fish rolls
directions: *Fish fillet suggestions:
flounder, pike or sole.

title: mexicano
directions: Line a large casserole with tortillas.
Layer the meat, onions, beans and cheese.
Cover with tortillas.
Spread soup over all, then pour can of tomatoes on top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
About 5 minutes before it is done, take out and spread cheese on top, if desired.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine
sugar,
syrup
and
water.
Bring to a rolling boil and
continue
boiling to 238°.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Beat egg whites and salt until stiff but not dry. Slowly pour syrup
over egg
whites
and
continue
beating until mixture becomes dull
in its
finish.
When loses sheen, add vanilla. Add nuts
and cherries.
Do
not
add nuts and cherries until vanilla is thoroughly mixed.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Then fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Combine next 3 ingredients in another bowl and mix well.
Add bowls together after about 1 hour.
Chill and serve.
Remix before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together.
Chill into 2 rolls.
Cut 1/8-inch slices and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl combine flour, baking soda, salt, ground ginger, crystallized ginger, allspice and pepper.
Mix well with a wire whisk.
Set aside.
In a large bowl mix sugar and butter with an electric mixer set at medium speed. Scrape down the sides of the bowl.
Add egg and molasses and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add the flour mixture and mix at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Chill the dough in the refrigerator for 1 hour; the dough will be less sticky and easier to handle.
Form dough into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheets 1 1/2-inches apart. Bake 24 to 25 minutes.
Use a spatula to immediately transfer cookies to a cool, flat surface.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Heat until it boils.
Add peanut butter.
Heat until smooth.
Stir in Rice Krispies until all Rice Krispies are coated with peanut butter mixture.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered cake pan.
Combine chocolate chips and butterscotch chips and melt in double boiler.
Pour mixture over bars in cake pan.
Place bars in refrigerator about 45 minutes, until chocolate topping is cool.
Cut bars now for easier cutting.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Mix together flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg and milk mixture.
Next add melted butter.
Bake immediately at 425° for 20 minutes in a square glass baking dish.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cook pork (shoulder is good) until well done.
Drain well, chop.

title: grilled honey mustard chicken with vegetables
directions: Mix honey and mustard in a gallon Ziploc bag to make marinade. Add cutlets.
Marinate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Mix olive oil, salt and garlic powder; coat vegetables with this mixture.
Heat barbecue.
Grill vegetables until slightly charred.
Grill cutlets until done.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook over medium heat, stirring all the time.
From the first bubble, start the time, then cook 5 minutes.
Pour this mixture over the next 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well using electric mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased dish.
Let set 2 to 3 hours before cutting.
Store in airtight tin.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Press crumb mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with mixer until creamy. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Beat well.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add egg whites. Add vanilla and set aside.

title: cordon blue
directions: Pound chicken breast.
Put on ham and cheese.
Roll and fasten with picks and fry until brown in hot fat.
Put in casserole and pour soup and cooking wine.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: california waldorf salad
directions: Soak the apple chunks in half the lemon juice.
Combine rest of lemon juice with yogurt, avocado, grated lemon rind and honey in the jar of a blender.
Puree until very smooth.
Toss together all ingredients with the dressing.
Taste to adjust lemon-honey balance (you might add additional juice or rind).
This salad is a meal in itself.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to box directions; set aside. Cover bottom of baking pan with chicken soup.
Spread chicken over soup and put stuffing on top.
Butter lightly and bake at 350° until stuffing is lightly browned.

title: mixed greens
directions: Strip greens from stalk.
Wash in cold water in which the salt has been added.
Wash 3 or 4 times in cold water or until water is clear of grit and sand; drain thoroughly.
In an 8-quart pot, put 2 quarts of boiling water; add rinsed salt pork or bacon and onion. Add all the greens, sugar and salt to taste.
Cover tightly and simmer 2 hours.
If frozen greens are used, simmer 1 hour.
Add crushed red pepper for extra flavor.
Serve hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: four layer delight
directions: Press first 3 ingredients into pyrex dish and bake at 475° 15 minutes.
Cool completely. Mix the next three ingredients until fluffy.
Put in dish and then mix the puddings with milk and put over.
Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and set aside.
Grate pepperoni and add to ground beef and brown.
Drain grease.
Add sauce and macaroni and 1/2 the cheese in a greased pan.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles.
While noodles are cooking, melt shortening in skillet and brown together onion and ground beef.
Remove from heat.
Blend together all other ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well and simmer together for a minute or two.
Add noodles after drained.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Grate cheese on top, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: black-bottom cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and salt together.
Add chocolate chips and set aside.
Mix together the flour, soda, 2 cups sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and cocoa.
Mix together water, vinegar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well and add to flour mixture. Fill muffin cups 1/2 full of chocolate batter.
Put 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick to see if cupcake is done.

title: donna's nut caramel fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk until it will thread. Remove from heat. Add flavoring and nuts. Beat until mixture is thick and creamy. Pour in buttered pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: boursin cheese spread
directions: Mix ingredients all together until fluffy in food processor or mixer.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Soften 1 hour before serving.

title: plum pudding steamed
directions: Steam 2 hours without opening lid on pan.

title: deep fried chicken breast
directions: Beat egg.
Mix all ingredients (except chicken) together.
Dip chicken pieces into batter and fry until golden.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sour cream, lemon, sugar, salt and dill weed; mix well.
Add cucumbers and onion; chill to blend flavors.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: In a stew pot, add water, bouillon cubes, chopped onion, broccoli and spices.
Boil 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add diced Velveeta cheese and whip until melted.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and cornmeal.
Drain pineapple.
Add to mixture with coconut and salt. Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding souffle
directions: Melt butter in a 6-inch deep casserole dish.
Beat the rest and pour into dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover 2 cookie sheets with aluminum foil (ungreased).
Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar, beat until stiff.
Add vanilla and salt.
By hand, add pecans, chocolate chips and Rice Krispies.
Stir real good!
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Put in oven, shut the door, turn oven off. Leave overnight or 8 hours.
Do not peak!
Remove cookies from cookie sheet with spatula.

title: english muffin delight
directions: Lightly toast muffins.
spread mixture on muffins.
Broil or toast until bubbly.

title: hot devil hash(feeds 4)
directions: Cut onions into 1/4 inch pieces.
Cut wieners into 1/2 inch pieces.
Put onions and wieners into frying pan with enough oil to prevent sticking and fry until onions are clear.
Mix and stir tomatoes with pepper.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot or slow cooker.
Cook 6 to 8 hours on low heat.
Before eating, bake the biscuits and when done, break each open and place on individual plates.
Dip devil hash over biscuits and you are ready to eat. Liquid hot sauce may be added to taste.
Serve with plenty of liquids.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl. Stir until potatoes are evenly coated.
Pour into a baking dish sprayed with no-stick cooking spray and bake, stirring occasionally, about 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: louisiana meat boat
directions: Brown meat and add flour.
Stir in onion soup, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Simmer.
Cut off tops of buns and scoop bread out of bottoms.
Spoon in meat.
(Can top with pickle relish.)
Top with cheese.
Put on bread top; wrap in foil.
Bake until hot at 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: With butter at room temperature, beat on medium speed, gradually adding sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Continue beating on low speed.
Add flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: honey bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald the milk, then add the honey and salt.
Add the egg and 1 cup flour and beat well.
Mix in the shortening, pecans and the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place the dough in a lightly greased bowl.
Grease the top of the dough, cover it and let it rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Punch down, knead and mold the dough into 2 loaves.
Put dough into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bundt cake
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and cherry pie filling.
Bake in sprayed or greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Make glaze with milk and confectioners sugar. Drizzle with small spoon when cake is cool or almost cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs very well.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Add lemon juice, oil, flour, baking powder and salt. Drop by teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: dr. pepper beans
directions: Pour beans in large baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Good cooked ahead and reheated.

title: beef and vegetable fajitas
directions: Place steak, onion, and red pepper in shallow dish.
Combine garlic, lime juice, oil, vinegar, coriander, cumin and salt.
Pour over steak and vegetables.
Toss, cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Preheat broiler.
Broil steak 8 to 10 minutes on one side; turn.
Add vegetables and remaining marinade; broil 10 more minutes, or until meat is done.
Cut meat at 45 degree angle in thin slices.
Mound steak and veggies in tortillas.
Fold and serve.

title: cheese and sausage appetizers
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cheese, butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat with electric mixer on medium-low speed.
Stir in cooked sausage.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix and pour into lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix in almost all of stuffing mix.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer chicken on top, then mix the 2 cans of soup with the 2 cups of chicken stock and pour on top.
Sprinkle the remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama's steamed chicken
directions: Salt, pepper and flour chicken wings.
Lightly brown in oil and drain on paper towel.
Slice the celery, onions and bell peppers julienne style about 1/4-inch thick.
Layer the chicken and vegetables in a pot and cover.
Pour chicken broth over all and cook on low heat for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: creole meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, rice, eggs, salt, pepper and Texas Pete.
Place 1/2 of the meat mixture in a baking dish; place cheese slices on top.
Put the rest of the meat mixture over the cheese slices. Mix the ketchup, sugar, water, vinegar and worcestershire; put this sauce mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Stir together the soup and water.
Mix hamburg, 1/4 cup soup mixture, bread crumbs, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into meat balls and fry in 1 tablespoon fat.
Add rest of soup mixture and cook for 15 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake 35 minutes in moderate oven.
Serve with Creamy Sauce.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift flour and 1/2 cup sugar 4 times.
Combine egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and extracts in large bowl.
Beat at high speed until soft peaks form.
Add rest of sugar in 4 additions, beating until blended.
Fold in flour in 4 additions with large spoon.
Do not beat.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake upside-down on rack.

title: cinnamon scent ornaments
directions: Mix the cinnamon and applesauce together until mixture forms a ball, adding more cinnamon if necessary.
Knead dough and turn onto a cinnamon dusted wood cutting board.

Roll out dough to 1/4 to 3/4-inch thickness and cut with your favorite cookie cutters. Poke a hole in the top with a small straw for hanging ornaments. Place on wire screen to dry, approximately 6 days.
Makes 6 medium size ornaments.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare instant pudding using 2 cups of milk.
Put in refrigerator.
Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese.
Layer in a sand pail as follows:
half of pudding, half of cream cheese mixture and half of crushed Oreo cookies; repeat.
Serve with a toy shovel.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Make a well in center of mixture; pour in buttermilk.
Mix lightly for 30 seconds.
Knead on floured surface for 30 seconds.
Pat dough to 1/4-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake immediately at 450° for 15 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: uncooked peach pie
directions: Bake pie crust shell.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream well and put in crust.
Arrange peaches on top of cream cheese.
Combine boiling water and other 1/2 cup of sugar.
Add cornstarch and cook until thickened.
Add a few drops of yellow food coloring to give a better color.

title: creole crab and rice
directions: Cook rice.
Melt butter in medium skillet over medium heat. Add onion and green pepper and cook until translucent.
Add tomatoes, Cajun seasoning, pepper, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf and cloves.
Bring mixture to simmer and reduce heat to low. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove bay leaf. Stir in rice and crab meat.
Transfer to 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients well.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork (dip fork in water to keep from sticking).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spud and spice cake
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients for 4 minutes.
Then add eggs and beat real well.
Mix soda in buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk/soda mixture alternately.
Put batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: cheese-bottom biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and butter; spread evenly over bottom of two 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare biscuit mix according to package directions for rolled biscuits, using a tiny 1-inch cutter.
Place biscuits on cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: frozen apple salad
directions: Lightly beat eggs, sugar, pineapple juice, lemon juice and salt and cook until it thickens.
Cool.
Mix apples, celery, crushed pineapple (drained) and nut meats.
Whip cream and mix with dressing.
Combine other ingredients and freeze.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray a rectangular baking dish with Pam.
Peel onions and potatoes and slice.
Layer chops, onions and potatoes.
Apply salt and pepper to each layer.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cookies
directions: Stir ingredients until moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange raw beef cubes in a pan large enough to hold them in a single layer.
Cut potatoes, carrots, onions, and celery in good sized chunks, layer on top of meat.
Mix 8 ounce can of tomato soup with 1 can water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Last of all, scatter quick cook tapioca on top.
Don't stir in.
Seal tightly and place in 325° oven for at least 2 hours.
Even another hour doesn't hurt.
Don't peek during cooking time.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup milk.
Cover with corn flake crumbs.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle paprika. Bake about 25 minutes in oven at 325° to 350°.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all in a crock-pot or pot. Simmer for 15 to 30 minutes. Serve hot. May be refrigerated and heated by the cupful in microwave. May be doubled. Delicious!!!

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well
with mixer.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.	Bake at
about
20 minutes. Don't overbake.
One cup nuts may be added to batter or sprinkled on your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: southwest stew
directions: In skillet brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Place beef and remaining ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash figs and crush well.
Mix all ingredients in pot and place over heat.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour in jars.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Boil potatoes 10 minutes, drain.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Pour pork and beans over potatoes.
Brown beef, drain off fat and layer over pork and beans.
Pour tomato soup over all. Do not mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: In large skillet cook ground beef and onions until beef is browned.
Drain
off
excess fat. Stir tomato sauce, water and taco
seasoning
mix
into
meat
mixture;
heat through. Remove from heat. Beat eggs, stir in milk.
Add a small amount of
the tomato
sauce
mixture
to
the egg mixture, stirring constantly. Return
all
to skillet.
Stir in kidney beans, 1 and
cups Monterey
Jack and the crushed taco or tostada shells.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Top
with
lettuce, 1/2 cup cheese, tomato and olives.
Let stand
to 10 minutes before cutting into squares. Makes 6 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; remove stem ends.
Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge tomato slices with flour mixture.
Brown quickly in shortening on one side; turn. Reduce heat and cook until slices are soft in center.
Remove to hot platter; serve hot.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cook chocolate, sweet milk, 1 egg yolk and 1/2 cup sugar together until thick like cream.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in milk and add, then add mixture from preceding.
Add flour a small amount at a time, mixing well each time.
Add flavoring and fold in beaten egg whites and bake in layers.
Makes 3 (8 1/2 x 1-inch) layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter crackers
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave in a microwave-safe bowl, stirring every 20 seconds until completely melted. Sandwich 2 crackers together with a generous amount of peanut butter. Press together so peanut butter spreads to the edge. Dip crackers into melted chocolate and place on wax paper to harden.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and mustard in bowl; blend well. Spread sauerkraut in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over top.
Top with sausage, then cheese.
Combine crumbs and oleo; sprinkle over top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are tender.

title: garlic thai chicken
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine soy sauce, garlic, sesame oil, red pepper and coriander.
Set aside.
Cut chicken into about 1-inch chunks, then add to the soy sauce mixture.
Toss lightly to coat, then set aside.

title: chicken dijon(low-fat)
directions: Combine yogurt and mustard.
Spread mixture over chicken in a shallow baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Each serving contains only 190 calories and less than 4 grams of fat.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Beat egg whites and jello until they hold a definite peak.
In saucepan, mix sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook to a boil and cook to 250° on candy thermometer.
Pour this over egg white mixture in a slow steady stream, beating constantly with your electric beater. Continue to beat until candy holds shape and loses its' gloss. Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper or place in well buttered dish and cut in squares.

title: asparagus green pea casserole
directions: Put asparagus in bottom of casserole dish, then add peas.
Mix juice from peas with soup and pour over asparagus and peas.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cover with cheese and bread crumbs. Cook until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients all together.
Spread lightly in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese and potato chips on top and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Rinse and drain beans. Place in large saucepan. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Core mushrooms with small paring knife to make a pocket in each one.
Rinse mushrooms thoroughly and set on paper towels to dry.
Lightly brown sausage in medium frying pan.
Remove from heat and drain well. Add cheese, onion and spices.
Mix well. Fill each mushroom with mixture. Bake in ungreased baking pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: classic walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine eggs, sugar, flour, corn syrup, butter and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Arrange walnuts on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° for an additional 35 to 45 minutes until center is set.
Cool completely.

title: aunt irene's chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Put celery seed, sugar, onion salt, paprika and dry mustard in small mixing bowl. Add; alternating 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1/4 cup oil until vinegar and oil are used up, beating hard after each addition. Continue beating until dressing thickens. Serve on bibb lettuce with pineapple and mandarin oranges. Broken walnuts can be added, also.

title: vegetable soup(meatless)
directions: Place all ingredients in pot and warm until vegetables are cooked (tender).

title: chicken ole
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce, corn, chilies, chili powder and onion powder.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
To serve, spoon over tortilla chips and top with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rigatoni and broccoli salad
directions: Drop the broccoli into a kettle of boiling salted water and cook until tender, about five minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
In same kettle of boiling water, cook rigatoni.
When water returns to boil, cook about 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and run briefly under cold water.
Drain well.
Put rigatoni in large mixing bowl.
Add the broccoli, the remaining ingredients and salt to taste to the rigatoni.
Toss well.
Serve at room temperature. Serves 6 for a main course.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Remove crust from bread and place on bottom of well-buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Blend together eggs, milk, chocolate syrup and water; pour over bread.
Push bread down slightly to soak up chocolate mixture.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes, pushing bread down in mixture occasionally.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled and top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: baked cinnamon french toast
directions: Line the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 6 slices of bread.
Butter remaining bread.
Place butter side up over bread in pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, cream, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over bread.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Place the dish in a larger baking pan.
Pour boiling water into larger pan to a depth of 1-inch.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes, until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Top with preserves and whipped cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Stir and simmer for two minutes.
Add tomatoes, soy sauce and sugar. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese and onion bites
directions: Spread each slice of bread with mayonnaise and layer of onion. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Arrange on cookie sheet; place under broiler until cheese is hot and bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Cook everything except cabbage.
Add drained hamburger and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shredded cabbage. Bring to a boil and simmer until thickness desired.

title: banana spice bread
directions: In medium bowl, mix together bananas, eggs and butter. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves. Add banana mixture; blend well. Stir in nuts. Place in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from loaf pan. Cool completely before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: oven scampi(serves 4)
directions: Combine and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cook 1/2 pound linguine al dente and drain. Pour shrimp mix over pasta.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve with extra Parmesan cheese and lemon slices.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and Crisco.
Add water, vinegar and beaten egg; blend together.
Makes three 9-inch pie crusts.

title: reuben dip
directions: Cube Swiss cheese and add to crock-pot.
Drain sauerkraut and add to crock-pot.
Add Thousand Island dressing.
Chop corned beef and add to crock-pot.
Heat until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Serve with cocktail rye bread.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a large Dutch oven or regular soup kettle.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Let soak 8 hours; drain.
Saute onion, green pepper, garlic and pimento in olive oil until tender.
Combine beans, vegetables, 5 cups of water and next 4 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.
Garnish with grated cheese, chopped tomatoes, chopped green onions and a dollop of sour cream. Yields about 8 servings.

title: peach crumble
directions: Pour peaches and sugar into 9 x 9-inch square pan; mix.
Mix together all other ingredients and sprinkle over the top of the peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: cathedral window candy
directions: Put marshmallows and coconut in a large bowl.
Melt butter and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
When melted, stir in eggs (while still over hot water).
Then add powdered sugar.
Cool. Pour the mixture over the marshmallows and stir well.
Line a waxed paper box with waxed paper and pack the mixture into that.
It makes 2 bars if a smaller box is used.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water for 15 minutes. Drain and season with seasoned salt. Reserve 1/4 cup of the broth.
Saute mushrooms in margarine until soft.
Mix broth with chicken soup.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

Put broccoli spears around chicken. Add mushrooms. Spoon soup mixture over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered with foil, and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: english muffin bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 3 cups flour, undissolved dry yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Combine milk and water in a saucepan. Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°). Gradually add to dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf dishes which have been greased and coated with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops of loaves with additional cornmeal.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add nuts and bananas last.
Bake in a round cake pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In a large bowl, combine the vinegars, wine, vegetables, spices and meat.
Cover the bowl and refrigerate for 3 days.
Turn the meat twice a day.
To cook, remove meat, dry and brown in large pot.
Add and heat marinade in same pot.
Cover and cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat to a platter.
Strain marinade and put 3 1/2 cups of it in pot.
Thicken with a mixture of water, flour and sugar.
Add gingersnaps and simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Cut meat and add to marinade to keep warm.

title: date nut balls
directions: Put dates, coconut, margarine and sugar in pan.
Cook 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove, add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Butter hands and form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and place in a pie shell. Sprinkle nuts on top and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.

title: onion soup for one
directions: Peel the onion and slice into rings.
Fry them gently in the margarine, then pour over the vegetable stock.
Add bay leaf and peppercorns; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and wine.
Sprinkle with grated cheese of your choice.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into thin slices.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand for 30 minutes.
Dredge in cornmeal.
Fry in shortening over medium heat until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: toffee crunch cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with mixer until creamy.
Add cake mix, eggs and water; beat until blended.
Stir in brickle chips and pecans.
Drop cookie dough by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are browned (top will look moist).
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spray 13 x 9 inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place bacon slices in bottom of baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on top of bacon.
Combine cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, sour cream, mushrooms and dried beef in large bowl.
Pour over chicken and bacon.
Cover baking dish with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco. Add eggs. Beat 2 minutes after each egg is added. Add rum and vanilla with last egg. Combine baking powder, baking soda and buttermilk. Add flour alternately with milk to sugar, shortening and egg mixture. Bake 1 hour at 350° in angel pan, greased and floured.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, lemon juice and celery. Cover and chill.
Add walnuts, mayonnaise and salt.
Toss lightly.
Serve immediately on lettuce.

title: mexican tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of beans on bread. Sprinkle with cheese, olives and onions.
Place a dab of sour cream on top.
Add slice of bread on top.
Pinch edges.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with salsa for dipping.

title: orange candied yams
directions: Place yams in pressure cooker with orange juice, rind, brown sugar, butter and salt.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool cooker at once.
Boil liquid until thickened and pour over yams.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk. Add blueberries.
Mix in with a spoon, not beater.

title: mexicali meatloaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and bake.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour and cook over low heat.
Stir until bubbly, gradually adding milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese. Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in corn. Pour over cooked meatloaf.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: moms german potato salad
directions: First dice the potatoes, as if you were making mashed, boil until tender.
Cool in colander, chop hard boiled eggs in large bowl; then start adding mustard, onion, dill weed, salt, pepper. In same bowl add miracle whip, mix well until blended.
take cooled potatoes and gently fold into mixture.
Chill in fridge for 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: Cook chicken in pressure cooker until very tender.
Chop chicken very fine.
Do not grind.
Chop finely the other ingredients.
Mix well with chicken.
(May also use cooked turkey, lamb, tuna or salmon.)

title: hanky pankys
directions: Brown sausage separately and drain well.
Add cheese until melted.
Add Worcestershire sauce, oregano and garlic salt. Spread on party size rye bread and freeze on cookie sheet.
Put in bag when ready to serve, then put under broiler, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken in pastry
directions: Brown chicken breasts in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
