Save juice.
Mix last 6 ingredients.
Put a large spoonful of mix on breasts and wrap with pastry shells and seal.
Brush with egg. Bake 20 minutes or until brown.

title: corn and chicken curry with couscous
directions: In medium bowl, mix couscous with 1 1/2 cups broth.
Cover and set aside.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain juice from all canned fruit.
Pour fruit in a large bowl.
Add sour cream, coconut and marshmallows.
Stir and refrigerate until ready for use.

title: scotch shortbread triangles
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add extracts.
Combine flour and salt and blend into creamed mixture.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness to form a 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Then cut square in half diagonally.
Brush lightly with beaten egg. Sprinkle half of triangles with sugar crystals.
Sprinkle other half with almonds and press lightly into dough.
Bake on cookie sheet in preheated 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 56 triangles.

title: beets with pineapple
directions: Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan. Stir in pineapple chunks and syrup.
Heat, stirring, until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in butter, lemon juice and beets.
Heat, stirring, about 5 minutes, until heated throughout.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar in mixer bowl on high about 5 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Fold into pumpkin batter.
Spread on greased, floured pan or cookie sheet (10 x 15-inch).
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on cloth (sprinkled well with powdered sugar).
Roll cake in towel and cool on rack or fridge.
Don't let get cold, will crack!!
Unroll cake and spread with filling.
Roll cake carefully and store in fridge until firm.

title: moist corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Oil a 9 x 4-inch baking dish with canola oil.
Bake at 400° about 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
Do not overcook or the bread will lose its moisture.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix ingredients together and let stand.
Cut steaks with the grain into strips, approximately 1/8-inch thick.
Marinate in mixture for 1 hour.
Drain the strips and place very, very close together on wire racks, placed on foil lined cookie sheets.
Dry in slow oven to 160° to 170° for 12 hours.
If prepared correctly, jerky can be kept unrefrigerated in an airtight container indefinitely.

title: apricot and sweet potato pudding
directions: Place apricots in 1 cup water and bring to boil.
Simmer until tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Fold in apricots. Put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake in slow oven (325°) about 40 minutes.
Serve with cream.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spiced eggs
directions: Boil
eggs, remove shells and cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks and mash to smooth paste, adding mustard, butter, salt, pepper and sugar.	When well mixed, press into the cup-shaped egg whites, round the tops and sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Put broth, water, potato, celery, carrots, onion and parsley in large pot.
Bring to boil.
Add basil, salt and pepper to taste. Medium boil 45 minutes.
Add beans, corn and can of tomatoes. Simmer another 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
Let cool; spread pineapple over cake and then put pudding, Cool Whip and cream cheese (spread over cake).
Keep in refrigerator.
Make in a long pan.

title: honey's chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Mix other ingredients and add chocolate and butter.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except last 2.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix cheese and chips and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: "karonnie"
directions: You will need 1 casserole dish and 1 strainer.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Wash peaches and dry.
Rice cooked potatoes and cool until lukewarm.
Add one egg and mix.
Put approximately 1 1/2 cups flour on a board or counter.
Add the potato mixture and knead in flour until the dough is not sticky.
Roll out the dough until it's about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares.
Cover each peach with a piece of dough, pinching edges together and turning in hands until layer of dough is smooth.
Boil dumplings in salted water in a covered pot for 10 minutes.
Serve with melted butter, sugar and dry cottage cheese.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Degrease.
Use a paper towel to soak up excess grease.
Combine all ingredients into crock-pot on medium-high.
When cheese has melted, reduce to low.
Serve dip hot in crock-pot with broken taco shells or tortilla chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian chicken cutlets
directions: Pound chicken flat.
Coat chicken cutlets with flour.
In shallow dish, combine bread crumbs, oregano and salt.
In another shallow dish, combine egg and water.
Dip each cutlet in egg mixture and coat with crumb mixture.

title: ranger krispies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In large bowl, cream margarine, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until blended.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in rice cereal.

title: jambalaya
directions: Boil and debone large fryer.
Cut sausage in 1/2-inch pieces. Save stock fryer boiled in.
Cut up onions and saute in large pot (6-quart size) until tender; add sausage, garlic and mushrooms. Cook until tender.
Add chicken stock and water; bring to a boil. Add chicken and season to taste.
Add Kitchen Bouquet.
Add rice and cook until rice is done.
Stir occasionally.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Make sure all ingredients are at room temperature before beginning.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour and set aside.
Cream butter and cream cheese with extract and add sugar, gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour in fourths, mixing well until just blended after each addition. Chill dough in refrigerator 1 hour.
Shape into small balls or drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Chill until firm.

title: aunt eva's snicker salad
directions: Dice apples (leave peeling on).
Cut up Snickers into small pieces and slice bananas.
Stir into the Cool Whip and serve.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Bring to a boil, keeping at a rolling boil for two minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Add last three ingredients.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl; set aside.
Bring margarine, oil, water and cocoa to a boil in saucepan.
Add to flour mixture. Blend in vanilla, buttermilk and eggs to mixture.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes in oblong pan.
Mix frosting and have ready when cake is done.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender (about 1 hour).
Let cool. Reserve 2 cups broth.
Bone chicken and cut into small pieces. Saute onion in butter. Add broth, salt, pepper, garlic and chicken. Add chiles and soups.
Heat thoroughly. Cut tortillas into quarters.
In a 4 to 6-quart dish, arrange layers of tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese, ending with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine 1/2 cup oleo, 2 tablespoons cocoa, 2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup milk.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off stove and add 1/2 cup peanut butter, 3 cups rolled oats and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Drop on wax paper and let stand for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashion potato soup
directions: Using
quart pan, melt butter and stir in cornstarch to thicken.
Add milk/water mixture and stir until mixed with butter. Add
all other ingredients, chopped.
Allow to simmer until potatoes
are
cooked
completely.
Recipe
is
easily doubled and is very good reheated the next day!
Serves 4.

title: banana salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour, and salt in sauce pan.
Mix well.
Add eggs, vinegar, and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
You could add some yellow food coloring while cooking if so desired.
Take from heat and add butter.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Cream can be added to thin and make smooth after mixture has cooled.
Layer sliced bananas and mixture until gone.
Top with peanuts.

title: old-fashioned walnut cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar; beat in eggs and milk.
Mix flour with baking powder and gradually add to egg mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into greased 9-inch round pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; frost with White Satin Icing.

title: california chili
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in Dutch oven.
Add spices, tomatoes and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
(I add kidney beans and some spaghetti.)
It's optional.

title: sour cream chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream together 6 tablespoons of margarine and 1 cup sugar.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat slightly.
Add sour cream to mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until sides separate from pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: veggie chicken meal
directions: Season chicken with garlic salt and pepper.
Preheat skillet with water.
Place chicken in skillet; cover and cook on low heat about 40 minutes.
Turn once.
Boil frozen veggies in bag about 20 minutes.
Add veggies to chicken and cook remaining 20 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix 1/2 bottle grenadine, 2 cans orange juice and 2 bottles 7-Up in a punch bowl.
Add crushed ice to keep chilled.
Add syrup, orange juice and 7-Up as needed to keep punch bowl full.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 6 hours before serving.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Mixture will be dry. Reserve 2 cups of crumb mixture.
Press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan or 10-inch skillet.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Combine beaten eggs, milk and shortening.
Add dry ingredients; stir well until thoroughly blended.
Pour into greased pan and bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef and cheese spread
directions: Blend together and serve with crackers.
Add a little more beef or mustard for extra flavor.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Saute onion and garlic in small amount of oil.
Beat eggs and add onion and garlic.
Add Bisquick, salt, pepper, sharp cheese and zucchini; mix well.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon in medium pan. Mix ingredients with bacon in pan. Serve over Uncle Ben's rice.

title: "powerful good" grape wine
directions: For each jar, fill 1/2 full with grapes; add sugar. Fill to 1-inch of top with cold water.
Screw new enamal type lids on jars.
Store in a dark place for 90 days. Strain.
Chill.
Wine may be bottled and stored; the longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: barbecued beef ribs
directions: Place ribs on a rack in a shallow baking pan and roast in a 450° oven for 30 minutes.
In a small saucepan, combine all other ingredients and cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Set sauce aside.
Remove the ribs and rack from pan and pour off the fat.
Reduce oven heat to 350°.
Return ribs to the pan and pour sauce over them.
Bake uncovered basting occasionally, until ribs are tender, about 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.
These are lo-cal, low cholesterol and low-fat.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Cut together the flour and 1 stick margarine.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; do not drain tomatoes. Press "chopping" button on blender until it sounds smooth and not chopping any longer.
Makes 1 pint.
Refrigerate salsa.
Lasts 2 to 3 weeks.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Bake the cake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: root beer
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little warm water; put all ingredients in a gallon container and add water to make 1 gallon.
Place the container in the sun for about 3 hours, then refrigerate until cold.
The root beer will have zip and be very refreshing.

title: veg-al salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Pour over Veg-all and cubed cheddar cheese, toss lightly.

title: salsa(from mexico)
directions: Peel and chop the onion and mix it with the rest of the ingredients.

title: spicy fried apples
directions: Wash, quarter and core apples. Place in a bowl; sprinkle with salt and lemon juice. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: bulgur salad(a summertime favorite)
directions: Prepare the bulgur wheat in 2 cups of boiling water.
Let cool.
Chop the cucumber, tomato, black olives, onion and green pepper.
Mix together.
Add remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.

title: mint brownies
directions: In large bowl, beat all ingredients together at low speed. Add walnuts.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cockeyed cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well.
Make holes in mixture and put mixed liquid ingredients in.
Stir well.
Pour into greased pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the egg. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk, beating

smooth after each addition. Stir in cut rhubarb and vanilla. Pour batter into a 9 x 12-inch pan (greased). Combine white sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top of cake. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dijon honey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and keep refrigerated.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and
bake
at
350° for 1 hour, first half hour covered, second half hour uncovered.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Layer oysters in greased casserole dish.
Then mix bread with other ingredients.
Continue to layer.
Pour liquid from oysters, mixed with cream, over all.
Top with bread crumbs and paprika. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, salt and pepper. Mix together in bowl onion, soup and sour cream.
Pour over hash browns and cover with sliced Velveeta.
Crush corn flakes and put on top, then pour batter over all of corn flakes.
Bake on 375° for 30 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: medley of vegetables
directions: Mix and put in a 3-quart casserole.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks oleo and pour over top of vegetables.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked spareribs and sauerkraut with dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut spareribs into serving portions; place in the bottom of roasting pan.
Add sauerkraut and a little liquid.
Cover; bake in moderate oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach until thawed. Drain and cool. Melt butter. Stir in flour, milk, cheese (which has been cubed), spinach, salt, pepper and cottage cheese. Beat eggs until fluffy. Fold into mixture. Put into baking dish. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in casserole pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes and enough water to cover in 4-quart saucepan. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes, gradually stirring in salad dressing, cream cheese, onion powder, salt and pepper until light and fluffy.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes; mix with the next 6 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with a mixture of brown sugar, flour, margarine and pecans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Keep lid on casserole while baking.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and remainder of ingredients.
Freeze.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Place in a bread pan and refrigerate overnight.
Remove the loaf and slice.
Brown the slices on both sides.
Place in a baking dish.
Cover with undiluted soup. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: bisquick yeast pizza
directions: Crust:
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add to Bisquick.
Stir well and knead 20 times.
Let rise 5 minutes.
Spread out into a pizza pan.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix into crock-pot the cans of soup and rice. Place the chicken on top of the mixture. Cook for 3 hours on high or 4 hours on low. Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue pot roast
directions: Coat a 4 qt. flameproof roasting pan or Dutch oven with non-stick cooking spray and warm over medium-high heat.
Season meat with salt and black pepper and place in prepared pan.
Cook meat, turning, until all sides are browned.
Transfer to a plate and set aside.
Add onions, bell peppers, mushrooms and garlic to pan.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes more until tender.
Stir in barbecue sauce, water, molasses, and chili powder and mustard powder; bring to boil over high heat.
Add beef, reduce heat to low, cover and cook 1 hour. Add carrots, cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes longer, or until meat is fork-tender and cooked through and carrots are soft.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Put rhubarb in a deep baking dish. Combine oats, flour and brown sugar. Cut into margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over rhubarb. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour rice over chicken.
Mix water and soups.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in a covered dish.

title: panache's whole wheat bread(makes three 9 x 5-inch loaves)
directions: Generously grease a large bowl and 3 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans. Combine oats, hot water, molasses, bran flakes, butter and salt in another large bowl and blend well.
Leave at room temperature until cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse the shrimp.
Mix with cream cheese and add enough cocktail sauce for color and flavor.
Mix well.
Serve with Ritz or Club crackers.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Beat ingredients five minutes.
Add nuts if using them. Grease and flour tube pan, pour in cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, let cool for ten minutes, then puncture top of cake with fork or cake tester and pour glaze over cake a little at a time.
Let cake remain in pan for several hours before removing.
Cake can be refrigerated or frozen after removing from pan.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cook butter and onions in large skillet.
Add chilies.
Add and stir constantly cheese.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.
(If cheese becomes too thick, thin with milk.)
Yields 20 to 25 servings.

title: palm beach burgers
directions: *The egg helps to hold the meat together.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown beef and drain.
In large skillet saute onion, cabbage and celery.
Place meat and vegetables in a Dutch oven. Add beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.
Delicious alone or served over rice.

title: crab sandwich
directions: Mix in bowl the crab; add salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Add celery, onions and enough mayonnaise to stick together.

title: no-fail fudge
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large saucepan, combine the first 3 ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently. Reduce heat; simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and chocolate chips; blend well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix ingredients together except chow mein noodles. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix noodles in before serving.

title: cream bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread 1 package of rolls on bottom.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on rolls.
Spread another package of rolls on top.
Put a little egg white on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute butter, onion, garlic and Cheez Whiz until melted.
Add soup and rice.
Add broccoli.
Stir well.
Put in casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all except crabmeat with a whip, then fold in crab very gently.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: southern baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook slowly in a 250° oven for about 4 hours.
Serves 12.

title: malayan chicken
directions: Heat oil and brown chicken completely.
Reduce heat to low and add everything but cornstarch and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes until fork tender.
Remove chicken to warmed plate and thicken pan juice with cornstarch mixed smooth into water, stirring over medium-low heat for 4 minutes.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: cinnamon fruit biscuit crunches
directions: Melt margarine.
Separate 10 biscuits.
Combine cinnamon and sugar.
Dip both sides of biscuit in melted margarine, then in sugar mixture.
Make a deep thumbprint in center of each biscuit. Fill with 1 teaspoon of preserves.
Bake in an ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (or a 9 x 13-inch pan) at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: glunk
directions: Brown onions and hamburger in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and sauce.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles until tender and mix in (after draining).
Then in a greased casserole, place 1 layer of Glunk, layer of cheese until you end with layer of cheese. Chill overnight.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 5 people.

title: applesauce-walnut cake
directions: Mix together applesauce, honey and oil in a large bowl. Separate eggs and beat in yolks.
Mix flours, baking powder, salt and spices in another bowl.
Combine with applesauce mixture and nuts.
Beat well for several minutes; then beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Spoon into a well-greased 9-inch square baking dish and bake in a preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: apple cheese appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add Cheddar cheese and onions.
Spread on apples.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.
Great for kids.

title: hot ham and swiss cheese sandwich
directions: Mix first 4 items together; spread a small amount of mix on to each side of hamburger bun.
Place one slice of cheese on bun. Place one slice of ham on bun.
Wrap each sandwich in aluminum foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable chips
directions: Scrub your choice of unpeeled vegetable well and cut into thin slices.
Place the slices in a single layer on a rack in a shallow baking sheet and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven until crisp and lightly browned.
Baking times will vary.
Start checking on the turnips and parsnips after 30 minutes; potatoes need from 40 to 50 minutes; beets 50 to 60 minutes.
Make just enough chips to eat in one day, if stored, they will soften slightly due to humidity.
Recrisp chips in preheated 300° oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: hot butterscotch sauce
directions: Heat to boiling in quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Serve over ice cream, pound cake, angel food cake, pies, puddings or baked custard.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oats to water.
Cover and let stand.
Mix shortening, white and brown sugars and eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix soda, salt, flour and cinnamon. Add this to sugar and shortening mixture. Add in oats.
Oats should be somewhat cool.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: skor bar dessert
directions: Bake German chocolate cake according to directions.
Bake in a square pan and use half of the cake for this recipe.
You can freeze half for another dessert.
Cool cake and cut into cubes.

title: pound cake
directions: Have margarine, eggs and milk at room temperature.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Add flavorings; beat well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
quart microproof casserole. Cover and place in
oven.
Cook
on
High for 5 minutes and then at 50 cook setting
for
13 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Stir before serving.

title: tennessee hopping john
directions: Wash peas and soak overnight.
Drain.
Fry salt pork, tomatoes and onion well.
Add 2 1/2 pints water, beans, rice, salt and pepper to season to taste.
Cook slowly in covered pot for approximately 1 hour or until all liquid has dried out.

title: jean's chicken sandwich loaf
directions: Combine chicken and tomato.
Trim 1/2-inch off ends of bread.

title: italian spaghetti sauce(meatless)
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add onions, bell peppers and continue to saute until soft.
Add squash and mushrooms and continue to saute until thoroughly mixed and heated.
Dissolve tomato paste in water and add.
Add all spices.
Stir over medium heat until mixed thoroughly.
Cover and reduce to simmer (lowest setting) for two to six hours (the longer the better); stir occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti or any other pasta.
This recipe makes at least 12 servings.
You may freeze the remaining sauce in dinner size servings for future use.

title: madeira cake
directions: Grease and line base and sides of 6-inch deep round cake pan lined with wax paper. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Cream the butter with sugar and lemon rind until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in lightly beaten eggs, a little at a time, beating well in between.
Carefully fold in the dry ingredients. Pour in cake pan and smooth over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then turn out and allow to cool on a wire rack.

title: mesquite grilled vegetable platter
directions: Combine oil and Mrs. Dash Mesquite Grilling Blend in a large mixing bowl. Add vegetables and toss. Preheat barbecue grill to medium heat. Place vegetables in a grill basket on barbecue grill (or hot skillet). Cook vegetables, turning 2-3 times until vegetables are tender and cooked through, about 15 minutes. Remove and place on a large platter, serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Put in cooked pie shell.

title: fruit with lemon gravy
directions: Mix all together including juice from cans.
This can be made with any combination of fresh and canned fruits (but must have juices from canned fruit).
The more fruit the more Jell-O is needed.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat milk until skin forms on top.
Pour over bread crumbs; add margarine and raisins.
Let cool.
Beat eggs slightly and mix with sugar, salt and spice.
Mix in cooled crumb mixture.
Pour in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
To test for doneness, insert a knife in the center.
It should come out clean.
The bread pudding can also be baked in a large loaf pan.

title: italian spaghetti and meat balls(this recipe came from an italian chef)
directions: Cook celery and garlic in a little shortening in skillet for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add to rest and cook 1 hour.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in a large roaster pan. Pour oil over crackers and stir well until oil has been absorbed. Place in warm oven (250°) for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and store in airtight container.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, pumpkin, soda, cinnamon and flour. Pour into a large greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle tea towel with powdered sugar. Turn cake out and roll in towel.
Let cool.
Beat with mixer the butter, cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Spread on cake when cool.
Re-roll and refrigerate.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Add strawberries.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: quiche
directions: Mix until mixture holds together.
Roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Make 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Place aluminum foil and beans, for weight, in each pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crumble Doritos in bag.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Reserve few for top.
Put browned hamburger and onion on top of Doritos.
Mix tomatoes, beans and soup together; put on top of hamburger.
Add cheese to top of mixture; sprinkle few Doritos on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Bring broth to boil and add the cream of chicken soup and black pepper.
Mix cold water, egg and oil with plain flour until a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut in thin strips.
Drop in boiling broth.

title: refrigerator or frozen pickles
directions: Refrigerate for 2 hours the cucumbers, onion and salt.
Drain.

title: gourmet strawberry pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over simmering water or in microwave and spread in thin layer over bottom and up sides of pie shell.
Set aside to harden completely.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Gently stir salt into cucumbers with ice cubes.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours or until cucumbers are crisp and cold.
Add more ice when melted.
Drain and add onions.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring quickly to a boil; Add cucumber mixture and bring to boiling; boil 5 to 7 minutes or to desired crispness.
Yield:
about 8 pints.

title: oreo surprise
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine milk and pudding; mix until smooth. Add sour cream and Cool Whip; mix until blended.
Crush Oreo cookies, add to mixture and mix well.
Pour into serving dish and chill.
You may top with crushed cookies, if desired.

title: george's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and chop eggplant.
Soak in salted water in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Soak bread crumbs in mixture of the two milks.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in margarine until tender.
Boil eggplant until nearly tender.
Drain well.
Mix bread crumbs, eggplant and sauteed vegetables.
Add eggs, salt to taste, pepper, sage and pimento.
Blend well.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
This allows it to brown.

title: ethiopian spiced tea
directions: Bring to boil water, cinnamon, cardamon and cloves.
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
You should be able to smell the spices.
Add tea and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Tea is quite sweet in Ethiopia as it is the "dessert" after a meal.
Tea is also served with plain bread for breakfast or just enjoyed as a snack.
At snack time, it is tasty with "dabo kolo."

title: salad
directions: Put
pineapple
and jello and 2 tablespoons sugar in pan and cook for 5 minutes.
Let cool and add cottage cheese, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix well eggs, sugar, oil or shortening, salt, baking powder and flour.
Put 2/3 dough in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread can of blueberry pie on.
Add a little milk to spread easier.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cut each carrot crosswise in half. In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in 1-inch of boiling water, heat carrots to boiling; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender; drain.

title: seasoned steamed broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into thick lengthwise slices.
Heat oil in skillet; saute onions and broccoli.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; cook 5 minutes over low heat.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ice cream.
Press 1/2 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Spread with ice cream.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over the ice cream.
Freeze for 4 to 6 hours. Serves 12.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together the soup, water or wine and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over noodles, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oatmeal blueberry muffins
directions: Note:
An additional 1/4 to 1/2 cup sugar may be added for sweeter taste.

title: raisin custard pudding
directions: Put bread cubes and raisins in 8-inch round bake dish.
Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Pour over raisins and bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix cracker crumbs and brown sugar; sprinkle on top, then bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine Cool Whip, pineapple and cottage cheese; sprinkle Jell-O over mixture.
Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook 10 minutes; stir constantly.
Put in jar hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, butter, cornmeal, milk, vanilla, juice and rind.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until set and lightly browned.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except corn flakes. Pour onto a 9x13 inch casserole and top with crushed corn flakes. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo in electric skillet.
Add broccoli and onion.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Heat thoroughly.
Add rice.
Turn skillet on 2 and keep warm.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg, then applesauce.
Sift flour, spices, cocoa and salt together and mix with raisins and nuts. Add alternately with hot water to which soda has been dissolved. Bake in loaf pan 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; let cool.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, pineapple juice, celery and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish or in a mold.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Dice bacon while still raw and not separated.
Fry until crisp.
Mix broccoli, onions, and raisins.
Before serving add bacon and sunflower seeds.

title: easy parmesan garlic chicken(prep. 5 minutes; total time: 30 minutes.)
directions: Mix cheese, garlic powder and salad dressing mix. Moisten chicken with water; coat with cheese mixture. Place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter and add 1 can cream of chicken soup with water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour uncovered.
tags: cream of chicken soup with water

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread chicken breasts flat; fold ham and cheese to fit and fold breast over.
Secure with toothpicks.
Mix flour and paprika and coat chicken.
In a large skillet in hot butter (margarine) over medium heat, cook chicken until brown on all sides.
Add wine and bouillon.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken to platter after removing toothpicks.
In a cup, blend cornstarch and cream until smooth; gradually stir into skillet.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over chicken.

title: cranberry nutmeg loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Makes sheet cake (9 x 13-inches) or 2 loaves.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolk (well beaten) and add milk.
Sift together flour, nutmeg, baking soda and stir into sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Then fold egg whites into batter.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes (sheet cake) or 55 minutes (loaves) or until brown and firm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well together and refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs in a large bowl.
Melt shortening or butter on low heat, add cocoa and blend well.
Pour chocolate and vanilla mixture into a bowl with sugar and eggs; mix well.
Gradually add flour until well blended.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add catsup, brown sugar and vinegar and stir.
Add beans; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 4 quarts.

title: asparagus and egg casserole
directions: Slice eggs and arrange in square or oblong baking dish.
Place asparagus in groups of 4 servings over eggs.
Add 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour soup over all.
Add remainder of cheese and cover with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holly wreath cookies
directions: Melt together over low heat: 6 tablespoons butter, 30 large marshmallows or 3 cups miniature and green food coloring.
Add corn flakes.
Drop into mounds and place 3 red candies for holly.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown ground meat, salt and pepper.
Add garlic salt; drain meat.
Add mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes with green chilies, onion or onion salt.
Mix together.
Layer with corn tortillas, meat mixture and grated cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Saute with butter the peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Add bread and salt and pepper.
Mix together with a splash of milk.
Mix chopped meat with milk, eggs and bread crumbs.
Pat half of meat in baking dish, stuffing in middle and rest of meat on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Put precooked (canned) ham in Reynolds oven bag.
Cover and cook on high 1/2 hour.
Turn to low for 6 to 8 hours.
This method can also be used for small turkey breast.

title: any flavor pie
directions: Mix defrosted frozen juice (no water added) with Eagle Brand and whip cream (large). Mix with spoon until blended well. Pour into the 2 pie shells. Refrigerate. Serve with a spoonful of whip cream on top of each slice or spread whip cream on top of whole pie after it has been in refrigerator for at least 1 hour. (Drained fruit and chopped nuts are optional to pie filling.)

title: ham and swiss soup
directions: In saucepan, melt butter. Whisk in flour until smooth. Gradually add broth. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Add the broccoli and onion; cook and stir until crisp-tender. Add the ham, cream and thyme. Heat through. Stir in the cheese until melted. Yield: 2 servings.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Mix sugar flour and salt.
Add lemon juice, melted butter and beaten egg yolks.
Add milk and stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Combine apple slices with sugar, quarter-cup flour, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Spoon into pie plate.
Place pastry on top of apple filling.
Seal edges and flute.
Cut several large slits on top to allow steam to escape.

title: tomato chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover; remove and debone. Saute onions and pepper in butter.
Stir in cheese, peas, and tomatoes.
In a large casserole, combine chicken and tomato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of shallow baking dish.
Add alternately squash, salt, pepper, onions, bread crumbs and cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Pour over the top, the evaporated milk and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until nicely browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook eggs, sugars, flour, pineapple, and water into a custard, stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add oleo, vanilla, and pecans.
Place layer of graham crackers in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 custard over graham crackers.
Repeat layers.
Add one final layer of graham crackers on top.
Chill.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops that have been dipped in flour.
Melt 1 beef cube in boiling water and grease from chops.
Combine potatoes, onions and broth in big baking dish.
Place browned chops on top of all. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until potatoes are soft and chop finished.

title: cabbage stew by james
directions: Stew cabbage, onion flakes and picante with enough water to make desirable amount of liquor.
Add sausage and rice.
Cook together 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve with garlic toast or cornbread.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 or 8 x 8-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 12 hours. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Double for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Put peanuts in bottom of crock-pot, then the chocolate bark, then German chocolate, white chocolate, then chips.
Cook for 2 hours.
Stir until well mixed and smooth.
Drop onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: green chili sauce
directions: Heat shortening in skillet on medium heat.
Saute onions in shortening.
Add flour and cook for 1 minute.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, cornstarch or flour, spices, butter, salt, egg yolk; then add milk.
Add beaten egg white last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in 400° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplants 1/2-inch thick and dip in flour, then in beaten egg and again in flour.
Brown slightly in 2 tablespoons oil.
Drain and layer in 13 x 10-inch baking pan.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over top.
Top with chopped onions and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: swans' cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add cream cheese; beat.
Add oil; beat.
Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Beat.
Add 2 eggs; beat.
Add 1 cup flour; beat.
Add 2 more eggs; beat.
Add 1 more cup cake flour; beat.
Add 2 more eggs; beat.
Add 1 more cup of flour; beat, then add 1/2 cup flour and vanilla.
Beat.
Add other flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not preheat oven.

title: peach-almond pound cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well medium speed with mixer. Add eggs one at a time beating after each addition.

title: hot mocha
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat (do not boil) top with whipped cream or marshmallow fluff.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare the cornbread mix according to the instructions on the back of the package.
Bake and allow to cool.
Crumble cornbread into a large bowl.
Fry bacon crispy; drain and crumble into the bowl of cornbread.
Add the cheese, ham, green onions, salt and pepper, then stir.
Add entire jar of mayonnaise and mix well. Cover and chill for one hour and serve.
Yield:

title: worcestershire chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut up chicken.
Wash and skin.
Salt to taste.
Flour each piece and place in a baking dish.
Place a small amount of oleo on each piece of chicken.
Do not spread. Saturate each piece with Worcestershire sauce and add water.
Bake for 30 minutes, then turn chicken and saturate with Worcestershire and bake until done.

title: gumdrop drop cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pasta with lemon cream and prosciutto
directions: Melt butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add shallots and saut until translucent, about 2 minutes.
Add broth. Simmer over medium-high heat until mixture is reduced to 1/4 cup, about 2 minutes.
Add cream, lemon peel, orange peel and cayenne. Simmer until sauce thickens slightly, about 3 minutes.
Add peas; simmer just until heated through, about 2 minutes.
Stir in mint and lemon juice.
Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper. Meanwhile, cook pasta in large pot of boiling salted water until tender but still firm to bite, stirring occasionally.
Drain; return pasta to pot.
Toss pasta with sauce to coat.
Divide pasta among plates or bowls.
Drape prosciutto slices atop pasta and serve, passing Parmesan separately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart pan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring, until mixture boils.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press in pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over hot water; pour over Rice Krispie mixture.
Cut into bars.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a skillet, crumble and brown the sausage; drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and line the bottom with cubed bread.
Top with sausage and cheese.
In a bowl, combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat well and pour over layers in the dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast smoothie
directions: Slice frozen banana into blender.
Add remaining ingredients to blender.
Whip until pureed.

title: fried potato patties
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Shape into 6 (3/4-inch thick) patties. Dip each pattie in egg and coat lightly with bread crumbs. Fry patties in hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat, 12 minutes or until lightly browned, turning once. Drain on paper towels.

title: fiesta baked cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese in large mixing bowl with electric mixer on medium speed to soften.
Reserve 1/4 cup shredded cheese for garnish.
Mix remaining shredded cheese, chilies, 1/2 cup sour cream and ground pepper into cream cheese.
Spoon into 10-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned around the edge.
Spread remaining 3/4 cup sour cream over baked cheese spread.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Garnish with bell pepper cut-outs.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip meringues
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until frothy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, continuing to beat.
Add vanilla, nuts, cornflakes and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in oil. Add chili powder, salt, catsup and water; simmer slowly for 1 hour. Add 2 cans of beans; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: grandma henson's meat loaf
directions: Soak crackers in milk. Add meat, onion, egg, salt, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Mix well and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sara's pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour slowly, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and almond extract. Put into greased and floured tube pan or 2 bread pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Delicious sliced, buttered and toasted for breakfast or topped with vanilla ice cream, strawberries and chocolate sauce for a super dessert.

title: carrot puff(sweet and smooth)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Place carrots in medium-size saucepan and cover with salted water. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Drain.
Place margarine, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla in blender.
Add carrots a little at a time and puree the mixture. Pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix and pour in freezer; finish filling with whole milk and freeze.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together well the sugar and Crisco.
Add to mixture the eggs, salt, soda, vanilla and flour; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts; mix well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet by 1/2 teaspoon full size.
Bake at 375° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain. Put in greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle herbed seasoned stuffing mix and cheese over the soup mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes on 350° or until fully heated.
Also, water chestnuts might be good in this recipe.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onions and sugar for 10 minutes.
Stir in flour until well blended with onions and the pan juice.
Add water, wine and undiluted beef broth; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Cut 4 (1-inch thick) slices of bread from loaf; save remaining bread to eat with soup.
Toast the bread slices in a 325° oven just until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.

title: tasty pork chops
directions: In a shallow casserole dish, place pork chops and top with onion slices.
Sprinkle few drops of lemon juice over onion. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: queen of hearts tarts
directions: You will also need nonstick muffin tins.

title: melt away sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, oil and both sugars.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients, adding flour last.
Roll 1 teaspoon of dough in a ball.
Roll in sugar; press down with a glass or fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: taco dip and chips
directions: Blend the taco seasoning, cream cheese and sour cream on medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Spread dip on serving plate.
Sprinkle on lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Grate carrots.
Add to kraut with chopped or diced celery, onions, pepper and pimento in a large mixing bowl.
Heat together the vinegar and sugar.
Pour over carrot mixture.
Cover and chill several hours before serving.
Put in jar with lid and refrigerate until it will keep for several days.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine 1/4 cup flour and sugar; mix with rhubarb.
Spread in buttered baking dish.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Combine oats, 1 1/2 cups flour and brown sugar; cut into batter.
Crumble over rhubarb.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If it seems too dry, add more stock. Salt to taste.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt pan.
Before putting in oven take some cocoa and make paste.
Pour on top of batter.
With knife, cut through batter several times.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: paula's party dip
directions: Combine all
ingredients and mix well.	Serve with corn chips. Time of preparation: 15 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Boil potatoes and mash with milk and butter.
In baking dish layer: ground beef, creamed corn, mashed potatoes and salt and pepper.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: doughnuts
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar and melted Crisco.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients, stirring only until smooth.

title: grilled ham-mushroom sandwiches
directions: In saucepan, saute mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter until lightly brown, stirring occasionally; remove from heat.
Stir in ham, sour cream, mustard and pepper; mix well.
Spread evenly on 4 slices bread.
Top with remaining bread.
Brush both sides with melted butter.
Broil in preheated oven until browned and filling is hot, turning once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: onion bake
directions: Combine 4 tablespoons butter with cracker crumbs; cover bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Saute 3 cups thinly sliced onions in remaining butter until limp and golden.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Soften margarine and mix well with the sugar.
Then add the eggs and flour and mix until smooth.
Add the buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
The baked pie freezes well and has the taste of a chess pie.

title: bea's dark pfeffernuss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, molasses and anise.
Blend dry ingredients; mix in gradually with hands.
If dough seems too soft, refrigerate until firm.
Mold into balls 1/2-inch to 3/4-inch in diameter.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake about 12 minutes or until golden brown on the bottom. Cookies harden on standing.
Store in airtight container with slice of apple to mellow them.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour in mixture.
Add chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Pour in greased oblong pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley dry seasoning.
Spread over cooled crescent rolls. Sprinkle chopped vegetables and cheese on top.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix wafers, sugar and margarine.
Stir in juice and nuts.
Roll into small balls and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.
Store 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in margarine until golden.
Stir in beef and seasonings.
Add mushrooms.
Saute until meat is done.
Add soup; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over biscuits, rice, noodles or baked potatoes.

title: mock pizza for cocktails
directions: Fry sausage, cut into small bits; drain. Cut cheese into small pieces.
Add to sausage to melt.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Spread on bread. Sprinkle garlic powder.
Freeze on cookie sheets. Store in plastic bags in freezer.
Bake as needed in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin sandwiches
directions: Cut pork crosswise into 4 serving-size slices. Place between 2 pieces of plastic wrap. Work from center and pound lightly with mallet to 1/4-inch thickness; remove plastic. In shallow dish, combine flour, onion or garlic powder and pepper. In another shallow dish, combine egg and milk. In third dish, place crushed crackers. Dip meat in flour mixture to coat. Dip into egg mixture. Coat with bread crumbs. In large skillet, cook slices in hot oil. Place on buns, serve with favorite dressings.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of cups; fill 1/2 full with cream mixture. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with pie filling while hot.
Serves 100.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in cold water. Chill until set but not firm.
While gelatin is chilling, dissolve remaining gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water. Blend in applesauce, sour cream and cinnamon. Chill until mixture starts to thicken. Spoon onto first gelatin.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold and garnish with salad greens.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out pie crust to fit a 9-inch pie plate.
Crimp edges decoratively.

Refrigerate until ready to use. Melt chocolate in microwave container at full power (100%) 3 minutes or in double boiler over simmering, not boiling water. Beat corn syrup, eggs, brown sugar, salt, vanilla and melted chocolate in a bowl until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until set in center.
If crust or top is browning too quickly, tent with aluminum foil during the last 15 minutes.
Let the pie cool completely.
Garnish with the whipped cream and pecans.

title: oatmeal-chip cookies
directions: Mix well the first 9 ingredients.
Then add chips and pecans. Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Prepare ground beef as you would for tacos.
Place the 6 tortillas on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slightly curve them up the sides and ends of dish.
Put taco meat over tortillas.
In same skillet, heat Ro-Tel and both soups to combine.
Pour over taco meat.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cheese is your choice, but I use Velveeta cheese.
Tastes great hot, but is better if left to cool until set.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Saute onion for 2 to 3 minutes or just until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and blend well.
Cover.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender and most of liquid has been absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Yields 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Cream all ingredients together and spread on chicken.
Bake 25 minutes at 425° and then for 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not turn.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients (with a fork), then add the next 6 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 50 cookies.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix well and put into graham cracker pie crust.

title: sugar peanuts
directions: Put all ingredients in frypan on high and stir while peanuts eat up water and sugar.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° in a preheated oven, stirring every 10 minutes for 30 minutes.

title: swiss bliss
directions: You will need a 20-inch piece of heavy-duty Reynolds Wrap. Spread center of Reynolds Wrap with margarine.
Cut steak into serving portions.
Arrange on foil, slightly overlapping each portion.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix, mushrooms, green pepper, tomatoes and season.
Mix juice, A.1. sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over meat and vegetables.

title: manicotti with spinach
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Ricotta cheese with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, the Mozzarella cheese, eggs, spinach, salt, pepper and garlic.
Blend well.
Cook manicotti shells al dente. Drain.
Fill with spinach mixture.
Place in baking dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes, until heated through and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: mom's southern pecan pie
directions: *Save enough half pecans for tops of pies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Set aside to cool.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: dorothy's dessert or salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Cut in squares.

title: berry mato jelly
directions: Bring tomatoes and sugar to boil; cook 15 minutes on low heat. Add jello and mix well.
Pack in pint or 1/2-pint jars.
Seal. Refrigerate overnight.
Store in freezer or refrigerator.

title: cheese steak(use wok or skillet)
directions: In large frypan, place oil, and heat to medium temperature. Add tomatoes and onion
and
cook
about
minutes or until wilted.
Add chicken, stirring several times.
Add milk, garlic, brown sugar, lemon juice,
red
pepper, salt, mace and bay leaves.
Bring to a
boil.
Cover
and
simmer,
stirring frequently, for 50 minutes.
Remove
cover
and
cook about 10 more minutes over high heat,
evaporating
most
of the liquid and until fork can be
inserted in chicken with ease.
Discard bay leaves before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's dynamite cheesecake
directions: Mush up with fingers and press firmly into bottom of spring-form pan.

title: spinach salad with apples and pecans
directions: Whisk together the first four ingredients.
Gradually whisk in olive oil, salt and pepper.
When ready to serve, toss salad dressing with spinach and endive.
Place on salad plate and add apple slices, crumbled Blue cheese and toasted pecan halves. Yields 6 servings.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Gradually add sugar and salt to beaten egg whites.
Fold in pecans until they are completely coated.
Melt margarine on cookie sheet; add coated pecans and spread out.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans. Add celery, onion, salt and pepper. Toss lightly. Mix oil, sugar and vinegar. Pour over bean mixture. Let set overnight in the refrigerator. Drain and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, margarine and milk and boil over medium heat 1 minute.
Turn off heat.
Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until well mixed.
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoon.
Let stand to cool.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Cut margarine into slices; place in pan.
Pour flour mixture over margarine. Pour fruit over flour mixture (heat fruit first).
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.

title: granpa cronin's irish party potato salad
directions: Chop potatoes.
Mix in bacon, olives, eggs, celery and Miracle Whip into large bowl.
Slowly add bacon drippings to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Add olive juice and mix well.
Season to taste. Serves 20.

title: applesauce-raisin bread(lo-cal and low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat the
oven to 325°.
Mix the applesauce, oil and sugar. Sift in the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix
well	after
each addition.
Add the egg and the raisins.
Mix.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour
and
20	minutes
or
until done.
One slice equals 180 calories.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix together brown sugar, pecans, pudding, sugar and cinnamon.
Dip rolls (frozen) in butter, then roll in sugar mixture.
Layer in pan.
Pour any leftover butter and sugar over rolls.
Cover; set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese, beaten egg and soda crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream oleomargarine with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well after each addition.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour salad oil over cooked macaroni in large bowl.
Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard, garlic salt and parsley.
Set aside. Toss vegetables with macaroni. Pour vinegar dressing over mixture.

title: chex party mix(large batch)
directions: Mix cereal nuts and pretzels in a large baking bowl.
Mix oil, worcestershire sauce and garlic salt together and pour over cereal.
Mix well.
Bake at 225 for 2 1/2 hours, mixing every 15 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: bootleggers beans
directions: Fry diced bacon and brown onion.
Drain off grease; add pork and beans, brown sugar, vinegar and catsup and stir well and cover.
Let simmer for 20 minutes or bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: paul's french toast
directions: Preheat griddle, electric skillet or regular skillet.
Spray with Pam.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Dip slightly stale bread quickly in batter.
Place on griddle and sprinkle cinnamon sugar mixture over bread.
Turn when bottom is browned.
Sprinkle cinnamon sugar on other side.
Remove from griddle when both sides are cooked.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream, salad dressing mix, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce well in mixer.
Add shrimp and blend. Serve with chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: coconut squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes in a 325° oven.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over first baked mixture.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes more.
To brown top, turn on broiler for a few minutes, watching carefully.
Then cut into squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, vanilla, eggs, lemon juice and salt.
Beat well.
Mix flour and soda in.
Blend apples and pecans in.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box, using egg whites and desired amount of coconut and pecans (chopped fine).
When cake is done immediately, pour in 2/3 of the can of cream of coconut.
(Be sure to shake the can up before pouring it.) Pour it into fork holes made all over the cake.
Let cool completely!
Ice cake with Cool Whip mixed with desired coconut and nuts and 1/3 can cream of coconut.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: buttermilk pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix melted butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour; let set a few minutes, until sugar melts some. Add buttermilk. Stir well and pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° few minutes; turn down to 325° until brown and bubbly.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients. Let stand 10 minutes. Heat oven to 350°.
Stir in egg whites until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan. Spread evenly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly. Cool. If desired, spread with your favorite cream cheese frosting. Refrigerate any remaining bars.

title: red enchiladas
directions: Save 1/2 onion.
Use large skillet.
Brown hamburger with 1/2 onion; drain grease.
Mix flour with hamburger.
Add tomato sauce and 3 to 4 cans water.
Season with chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Place tortillas in sauce; let soften for a minute or so. Place tortilla in plate with a little sauce.
Add lettuce, onion and cheese.
Make another layer if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: beef creole
directions: Partially freeze meat, then slice thin.
Fry in a Dutch oven or large pot in the shortening until brown.
Then remove from Dutch oven.
Saute onion until tender.
Then brown flour.
Add the tomatoes, garlic, green pepper, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add the meat and 2 cups of water.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Heat milk, sugar and gelatin in top of double boiler over very low heat, stirring occasionally, until small bubbles form around edge of milk.
Stir in salt and rice.
Place over boiling water; cover and cook 1 hour or until rice is soft.
Stir in extract and cool to room temperature.
Whip cream and fold into rice mixture; chill several hours.
Serves 6.

title: grandma holiman's tea cakes
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients and add, making a soft dough.
(Use more flour if necessary.)
Roll thin and bake quickly at 400°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain apricots and pineapple, reserving liquid and add water to make 2 cups. Bring juice and pudding to a boil over low heat and cool. Pour over fruit. (Do not cut up bananas until ready to pour liquid over fruit.) Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar at least 10 minutes.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Place in large greased tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Turn on oven to 300°.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cake must be started in cold oven.
Let cake set 5 minutes before turning out.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and combine with the remaining ingredients. Simmer in a covered kettle until barley is soft.

title: jazzy jalapeno rice
directions: Combine first six ingredients and saute until onion is transparent.
Add 4 cups hot water with beef bouillon cubes. Simmer 35 minutes.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and confectioners sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust and freeze until ready to serve.
May add chocolate shavings to top.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Mix strawberries, sugar and jello.
Bring to boil (or until sugar dissolves).
Let cool.
Have milk cold and whip with a hand mixer until very stiff.
Fold in cool strawberry mix and put in vanilla wafer crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, 2 eggs, confectioners sugar and vanilla with electric mixer and pour over crust layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: deep fried chicken legs
directions: Put grease in deep fryer; heat until hot.
Add A.1. steak sauce in the grease, then add hot sauce to the grease.
Batter the chicken legs in flour, salt and pepper (put the salt in the flour).
Put the chicken legs in the deep fryer; fry until done.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a full boil, then boil 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate pieces.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and cool at room temperature.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream
butter
and corn syrup (Karo).
Do this by hand, do not use mixer.	Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add vanilla, salt and pecans and
mix.	Pour into 2 pie shells and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hospitality cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder, add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings. Pour batter equally into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove from pan and let cool on rack.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except oats, almonds and chocolate pieces.
Blend well with mixer.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
If desired, chill dough for easier handling.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together; add other ingredients.
Put layer of corn tortillas in bottom of casserole (cut in 1/4-inch strips); add a layer of mixture.
Alternate until all ingredients are used.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add corn flakes and oatmeal.
Add flour into which salt, baking powder, soda and coconut have been added.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: 15 minute soup
directions: Brown beef with salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain on paper towel.
Put in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and pretzels.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Combine the onion, green onions and egg and buttermilk mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients. Spoon into hot grease.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Move oven rack to low position so that the tops of pans will be in center of oven. Heat oven to 350. Grease bottom only of 2 loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 inches, or 1 loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3 inches, with cooking spray. Mix zucchini, sugar, oil, vanilla, and eggs in large bowl. Stir remaining ingredients. Pour into pans. Bake 8 inch loaves 50-60 minutes, 9-inch loaf for 1 hour 10 minutes to 1 hour 20 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pans on wire rack. Loosen sides of loaves from pans; remove from pans and place topside up on wire rack.

title: jello shots
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water, stirring until the Jell-O is dissolved.
Add liquor.
Chill until set in the plastic cups. Possible combinations:

title: raspberry ribbons
directions: Preheat oven 375°.
Combine butter, sugar, egg, flour, vanilla, salt and water.
Beat and mix well.
Divide dough into fourths. Roll each fourth into rope shapes about 14-16-inches thick.
Press groove down center with little finger.
Bake 10 min.
Spoon jam into groove.
Bake 5-10 min. longer.
Until edges are lightly brown.
In small bowl, mix powdered sugar and milk to make glaze. Drizzle over baked dough.
Cut into 1-inch slices while warm.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour and salt.
Add beaten eggs, milk and corn.
Put in well-greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Chip oleo on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Stir from sides while cooking.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put 1/2 of the box of cake mix in pan.
Pour the can of apple pie mix over cake mix, evenly.
Sprinkle remainder of cake mix over apple mix.
Pour 1 cup of water over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake top layer is done, or has a slight crust.

title: spinach artichoke casserole
directions: Add stick of butter to cooked spinach.
Add cream cheese. Stir into hot spinach until smooth.
Place artichokes (sliced and drained) in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Pour spinach mixture over artichoke hearts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Prepare 3 cups shredded cabbage.
Heat shortening in skillet. Add vegetables and stir.
Cover.
Steam 5 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring.
Add salt and pepper.
If desired, stir in 1 tablespoon soy sauce.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix soy sauce, Kitchen Bouquet and all seasonings.
Rub evenly over roast.
Chop and dice garlic.
In large iron skillet or Dutch oven, cook garlic in cooking oil.
Add onion and roast.
Brown roast on all sides over medium heat.
Add 1 cup of water and remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Cook slowly in 325° oven for 2 hours or until tender.

title: company casserole
directions: Early in the day, cook noodles and drain.
Saute ground chuck in margarine until brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat; add cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream and onion. In 2-quart casserole, spread half the noodles and half the cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Pour over the melted margarine and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: ~audry's cake~(this is wow!)
directions: 1) Mix (# 1 - 4) together *save 1/2 c dry cake mix. Spread 1/2 mixture in a 13 x 9 baking pan. You can use a casserole dish.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: georgia special
directions: *Cut oranges into 3 pieces before putting in batter.

title: cheeseburger potatoes
directions: Put oil in large skillet.
Peel and slice the potatoes.
Fry potatoes until nearly done and just beginning to brown.
Add onion and crumble ground beef over potatoes.
Continue frying, turning frequently, until meat and potatoes are done and browned. Season to taste.
Top with cheese and serve this to your kids along with a bottle of ketchup.

title: berry best blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 6 large, 3-inch muffin cups with nonfat, nonstick spray and set aside.
In a large bowl, stir together both flours, sugar, baking powder and lemon peel, making sure all is evenly distributed.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Mix pancake batter thin.
Put small pieces of turkey in the thin batter; cover completely.
Deep fry in hot oil until brown and crispy.
Delicious as finger food.

title: dump salad
directions: Just dump together.
Mix and chill.
You can freeze it and just as good as ice cream.

title: casserole
directions: Brown meat and mix with other ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
(If using uncooked rice, add 1 1/2 soup cans of water; can also add 4 tablespoons soy sauce and cover top with chow mein noodles.)

title: chewy dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling chicken broth.
Dumplings will rise when cooked.
Drain and fry in butter until heated through.
You may also add 1/2 pint sour cream when you are frying the dumplings.
When serving, sprinkle with paprika.

title: multi-grain pancakes with fruit(low-fat)
directions: Add melted margarine to milk, egg white and berry mixture. In separate bowl, mix flours, oats, sugar, salt and baking powder. Add the berry/milk mixture to the dry ingredients and stir lightly.
Lightly coat griddle with nonstick spray.
Cook on medium heat for 1 minute until pancake bubbles, then flip over for 1 more minute.

title: cracker-jack cookies
directions: Cream butter well and blend in sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together and mix in. Add oatmeal, coconut and Rice Krispies by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Wet bread with catsup, milk and mustard.
Add onion and eggs, then meat.
Mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Sprinkle 1 large package of orange jello into a pint of cottage cheese.
Add crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges, which have been drained.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill several hours.

title: fruit casserole bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter.
Add sugar, flour and curry to butter.
Lay fruit in a pan and pour mixture over it. Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together; let set at least 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mix all other ingredients and combine with squash.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until browned on top.

title: quick skillet supper
directions: Cook beef and onion in hot fat.
Place uncooked noodles over top of meat mixture.
Combine
remaining
ingredients and blend well.
Pour over noodles, taking care to moisten noodles well.
Do not stir.
Bring to boiling.
Turn
heat low.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: louisiana lima bean soup
directions: Wash lima beans.
Place in large kettle.
Add water and ham bone, onions and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer over low heat until the beans are tender.

title: eggplant parmesan
