directions: Peel eggplant and cut in round 1/4-inch slices.
Beat eggs with 2 tablespoons water.
Dip eggplant in Italian bread crumbs, then into eggs and again in bread crumbs.
Heat all in skillet and brown eggplant (drain on paper towel).

title: chess pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until crust is lightly browned and filling is completely set.
Cool at room temperature before serving.

title: maple muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add maple syrup; stir in eggs and applesauce.
Mixture tends to curdle.
Stir in flour mixture. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: dutch fruit pancake
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Add sugar, orange juice, fruit and cinnamon; cook until fruit is done.
Keep warm while preparing, eggs, salt, flour and milk.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Simmer chicken until done (save water).
Cool and pick chicken from bones; cut into pieces.

title: blueberry pie delight
directions: Use fork to mix.
Mix ingredients and spread on bottom of dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. COOL.

title: fiesta stack-ups
directions: Be sure to use all ingredients.
The sweet taste of the coconut and pecans really makes this a treat.
Will serve 20 hungry people.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour over oyster crackers.
Shake well. Bake at 250° until golden brown.

title: oatmeal black walnut cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg, butter and vanilla together.
Stir in dry ingredients and black walnuts.
Spoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes.
Let cool, then enjoy.
Makes 95 cookies.

title: peanut butter microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and peanut butter.
Pour in milk; place butter on top.
Cook in microwave for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir until blended.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Melt butter in heavy 10-inch skillet. Stir in salt and onion salt. Add Rice Chex. Let brown slightly, about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Add grated cheese and paprika and stir; cool and put in airtight container.

title: glazed peach chicken
directions: 1. Place chicken in 3 1/2 to 4 quart slow cooker; sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Top with garlic, chilies, sweet potatoes and onions.

title: baked butternut squash
directions: Spread butter over the cavities and cut surfaces of the squash and place in a baking pan.
Combine all other ingredients and sprinkle into squash cavities.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until squash is tender.
Serves 6.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine Eagle Brand and Cool Whip; beat well. Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix well, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix again and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until a knife inserted in the filling comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: mom's winter special
directions: For many years a man watched his wife take a locked box down from the cupboard.
She would unlock the box, take a pinch, sprinkle it over whatever she was cooking, relock the box and return it to its place.
One day, while his wife was away, his curiosity got the best of him.
He went to the cupboard, took the box down and opened it.
To his surprise it was empty.
He turned it over and on the bottom was written the word "love".
Don't keep your "love" locked up in a cupboard.
Keep it within easy reach and use generously.
So into everything you cook, put a pinch of "love".

title: worsley heavenly hash
directions: Mix together.
Let stand for 12 hours.

title: breaded steaks
directions: Flatten steaks to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into serving-size pieces; set aside.
Place flour in a large resealable plastic bag. In a shallow bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Place bread crumbs in another shallow bowl.
Coat steaks with flour, then dip into egg mixture and coat with crumbs.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, cook steaks in oil for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown and cooked to desired doneness.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 2/3 cups of boiling water; add other ingredients.
Let jell.

title: 4 layer pudding cake
directions: Blend the flour, butter, pecans and brown sugar.
Press into pan (13 x 9-inch) and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim fat off meat and cut into individual serving pieces. Pound, flour and brown meat in 3 tablespoons oil.
Remove from skillet when nice and brown.
Pour out drippings and wipe pan with a paper towel.
Return meat to skillet.
Puree canned tomatoes and pour over meat.
Add onions and celery.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add peas and carrots.
Cook 1 more hour.

title: golden pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 cup juice.
In a mixing bowl, combine pineapple and juice with sugar, flour and eggs; mix well. Spoon into 2-quart baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until set and browned.
Serve as a side dish with ham or poultry.
Yields 8 servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Saute ground beef in skillet until crumbly.
Add taco sauce. Simmer 15 minutes.
Layer corn chips, ground beef and cheese in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield: 2 to 4 servings.

title: herb and cheese bread
directions: In a food processor, combine reserved tomato liquid, margarine, 1 1/2 cups cheese, mayo, parsley, salt and oregano. Process until smooth.
Spread mixture evenly onto each half of bread.
Top with tomatoes, remaining cheese and basil.
Bake on 350°
for 10 minutes.
Broil until cheese is melted and bubbly. Slice into 1 1/2-inch slices.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage but do not shred.
In large pot, brown onion in oil just until soft, but not brown.
Add rest of the ingredients. Cover and cook slowly, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Add more sugar, if you like it sweeter.
Serve with slotted spoon.
Keeps well in refrigerator for days.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add flour and blend.
Add beet liquid; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Drain beets and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: fig-strawberry preserves
directions: Thoroughly mix figs, gelatin and sugar in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil over low heat and continue boiling for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour quickly into glasses. Cover at once with 1/8-inch hot paraffin or seal with new lids.
Makes 6 medium glasses.

title: tomatoes au gratin
directions: Lightly oil a baking dish.
Slice tomatoes horizontally in half, arrange the tomatoes, cut side up, in the baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with minced garlic and parsley, then with the combined cheeses and olive oil.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes, until the cheeses have melted and top is browned and bubbly.

title: cooked artichokes
directions: Wash artichokes, scrape and place in cold water.
Drain; add salt and boiling water to cover.
Cover pan and cook about 30 minutes or until tender.
To serve, season with butter and pepper. For 6. Dice artichokes and serve with browned onion butter.

title: capirotad(bread pudding)
directions: In a 6-quart pot, cook raisins in 2 quarts of water with the sugar added.
In a Dutch oven, pour 1/4 cup of juice from the raisins.
Then add 3 to 4 slices of bread, layer along with 1/2 cup raisins.
Then add 1/2 cup of shredded cheese.
Repeat layers to use up all ingredients.
Put on to cook on medium heat.
Pour the milk over the top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
If this looks dry, add a little more milk.
Cook until cheese is very well melted, but do not overcook.

title: mother-in-law's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix first 6 ingredients together well. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Decorate the top of the pie with pecan halves. Bake for 40 minutes or until set in the middle.

title: "possum stew"
directions: One possum gathered at sunrise by trained rednecks.
Use only the freshest road kill that has been run over by at least one log truck.
Heat all ingredients and serve.
Great by itself or with corn bread.

title: russian tea
directions: Slice oranges and lemons; cover with sugar.
Let stand 1 hour. Make tea with hot water and pour the tea over the fruit.
Add cloves and cinnamon.
Let simmer for 1 hour and serve.

title: cool veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Press onto bottom of 15x10x1-inch baking pan to form crust. Bake 11-13 minutes or until golden brown; cool. Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip, dill weed and onion salt until well blended. Spread over crust; add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate. Cut into squares to serve.

title: macaroni and chicken salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes elbow macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In medium bowl, combine macaroni, chicken, apple, celery, grapes and pineapple; mix well.

title: chicken log
directions: Mix together with hands chicken, cream cheese, onion, celery and mayonnaise.
Form into two logs and roll in pecans and parsley flakes.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Can put in freezer. Serve with crackers.

title: apple raisin coffee cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in the raisins.
Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over the apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 servings.

title: soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour round 8-inch cake pan. Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Fold in the eggs and sour cream.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Do not overbeat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in nuts.

title: peter's pot
directions: Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting in squares to serve.
Can be made the day before, adding crumbs at time of baking.
Leftovers are good cold.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: chicken and orange rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice mixture and sprinkle remaining onion soup mix over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits.
Place apples in center.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Fold and pinch dough to seal edges.
Place in Pyrex dish.
Place remaining chopped apples, if any, around dumplings.
Bring 7-Up, margarine and sugar to a boil until melted and pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or just until browned well and apples are tender.

title: cocoa balls
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, butter, salt and milk in a saucepan. Heat until it starts to boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.
Store in refrigerator in a tin or other container.

title: ragu easy pasta twist casserole
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Add hamburger and Ragu.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer 1/2 the pasta mixture in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Evenly spoon cottage cheese over pasta; layer 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese over cottage cheese.
Spoon remaining pasta mixture over cheeses.
Bake, covered with foil, for 30 minutes and uncovered for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese with 5 minutes left on the timer.
Serve with Parmesan cheese. Serves 6.

title: roast chicken lebanese style
directions: Wash roasting hen inside and out well.
Mix rice, meat and spices together.
Melt butter and cook pine nuts until light brown.
Pour all in with rice mixture and mix well.
Stuff the mixture into the hen and wind string around the hen to keep stuffing in.
Boil hen in large pan for 2 hours.
When done, put hen into roasting pan and bake slowly for about 1 to 2 hours. This is a very tasty and delicious dish.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, celery, butter, salt and pepper in large saucepan. Cover with just water to cook potatoes until they are tender; don't drain water. Add evaporated milk and cream of celery soup. Mix well. Cook for a few more minutes to heat through. Good with crackers or cornbread.

title: pineapple banana split cake
directions: Combine and press into large pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Cool.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beat 1 minute.
Put cocoa and coloring in cup and make paste.
Add to cream mixture.
Add salt, put vanilla in buttermilk.
Mix vinegar and soda in cup, add last to mixture and blend.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes after pouring into 2 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: cheese balls
directions: Chop beef and onions in blender or processor.
Save enough beef to cover ball.
Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Shape and refrigerate.
Cover with beef.
Makes 2 large balls.

title: hostess cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Make 2 round cakes and cut into 4 layers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring jello, sugar and water to a boil until sugar dissolves. Mix cornstarch with a little water to dissolve.
Stir into strawberry mixture (jello mixture) until thick.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour a little filling in bottom of pie shell.
Slice a layer of strawberries over filling.
Repeat layers ending with filling over top.
Chill in refrigerator about 4 hours.
Serve with whip topping.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand. Shape into small balls. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except wings) until blended, using large casserole dish or roasting pan.
Fold wings and add to sauce, wetting all of them.
Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep moist and basted. Serve and enjoy!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices. Stir in nuts, raisins and coconut.
Grease sides and bottoms of 4 (1 pound) coffee cans well.
Line bottoms of cans with wax paper. Pour mixture into cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool slightly and loosen sides of loaves from can.
Remove and cool completely before slicing.
To store, wrap and refrigerate no longer than 10 days or freeze until ready to use.
Yields about 32 slices.

title: chocolate butterscotch rice krispies
directions: Melt butterscotch and chocolate morsels along with peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in a covered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: speck fuller's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well; add Eagle Brand milk and both cans of Pet milk.
Beat well.
Finish filling to fill line of freezer with milk.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well except walnuts.
Place in casserole and sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: cheesy chicken breasts
directions: Roll chicken breasts in first 2 ingredients and brown quickly. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients except cheese and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Uncover, sprinkle cheese over top and return to oven, uncovered, for 20 minutes more.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: honey-glazed carrots
directions: In

medium saucepan over high heat, bring honey, butter, bourbon and water to a boil. Add carrots. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes or until liquid is reduced to a glaze and carrots are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: cookie fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough on greased pizza pan and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: picnic macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed elsewhere on package.
Drain and cool.
Combine macaroni and remaining ingredients, toss lightly. Chill and serve.

title: turnip slaw
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add mustard seed, horseradish and turnips.
Stir well.
Let stand several hours before using.
Put in Ziploc bags and store in the freezer.
This keeps well and freezes well.

title: cream of reuben soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion, celery and caraway seed in 2 Tbsp. butter or margarine until slightly soft.
Add chicken stock or chicken broth and bring to a boil.
In a small saucepan, melt 1/2 c. butter or margarine, stir in flour.
Mix well and add to the boiling soup, stirring to combine thoroughly.
Reduce heat to a simmer.
Stir in sauerkraut and corned beef.
Add salt and white pepper to taste.
Just before serving, add half and half or light cream. Heat, but do not let soup come to a boil.
Serve immediately.
This holds well in a Crock-Pot.

title: corn  scallop
directions: Do not drain corn.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350 degrees 35 to 40 minutes in a 11 x 7-inch dish.
Puffs up with crusty top.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and boil until transparent, stirring most of the time.
Add jello and boil again. Cool.
Pour over strawberries in crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift the flour with salt and soda.
Thoroughly mix the shortening, sugars and egg until light and fluffy.
Add flour and rest of ingredients.
Mix until well mixed.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: texas cornbread dressing
directions: Soak cornbread and white bread in broth in a large bowl about 10 minutes.
Stir until liquid is absorbed.
Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Add sausage and cook over low heat until sausage is browned.
Drain.
Add mixture to bread mixture. Add eggs, salt and pepper; mix well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish in a 350° oven for 45 minutes until lightly browned. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together will.
Store in 1 gallon sealed container.
Mix 1/3 cup of the cocoa mix with 1 cup of hot water.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Beat eggs with a whisk and put in pan.
Sprinkle with onion flakes, pepper, dill weed and parsley; stir into eggs.
Add 1 tablespoon cottage cheese and stir again. Put shredded cheese (Cheddar) on top; cook until the cheese melts.

title: south-of-the-border bean and bacon pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Unroll dough and place in a greased pan.
Starting at center, press out with hands.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Barely cover potatoes & onions with water, boil for 20 minutes or until mixture starts to thicken.
Add cream of celery soup and bring to a boil.
Add cheese, thyme, salt & pepper.
Cook until creamy.
Serve with bacon bits, chives or sour cream.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Add 2 cups flour
and milk, alternately.
Add cherries and raisins. Add
nuts which have been dredged in 1 cup flour and cinnamon. Pour into pans and cook about 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool. Top with coconut or cream cheese frosting.

title: maple glazed acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Halve squash and remove seeds and fiber.
Place in a shallow baking pan, cut side down.
Add 1/2-inch water to the pan and bake 30 minutes.
Remove squash from the pan, discarding water.
Trim a small slice from the bottom of each squash so that it will sit straight in the pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon into squash centers.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes, basting frequently.
Good with pork or poultry.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter and chocolate balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and make balls.
Stick toothpick in each and set in refrigerator for 30 to 60 minutes.
Then, melt large box of chocolate chips and 1/2 block paraffin in double boiler over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Dip each ball in chocolate and set on wax paper.

title: singapore chicken wings
directions: Mix all together.
Dip wings into sauce.
Place on cookie sheet.
Pour remainder of sauce over wings.
Marinate 2 hours in refrigerator, turning at least twice.
Also can be left overnight. Bake in 375° oven.
Baste and turn at least 1 time during baking. Great over the campfire.

title: martha's sweet potato bread(yield:  2 loaves)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients, except pecans.
Combine dry ingredients with mixture. Do not overmix.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add the eggs and vanilla and beat. Add flour, soda and dry pudding. Mix well and add chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir pretzels with sugar into melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put into buttered baking dish; top with shredded cheese and chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: For marinade:
Combine 2 teaspoons soy sauce, 2 teaspoons sherry, 2 teaspoons cornstarch and salt in large bowl; mix well. Add chicken; stir to coat well.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: spiced pickled eggs
directions: In saucepan, bring eggs to a boil.
Remove from heat and close tightly.
Let stand 20 minutes. Drain and run cold water over eggs until chilled.
Peel.
Combine allspice, ginger, cloves, red peppers and garlic in cheesecloth.
Tie loosely.
Combine vinegar, water, salt and sugar in a saucepan.
Put in spice bag.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard spice bag. Pour over eggs.
Refrigerate.
Ready to eat in 2 days.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Store in airtight container. For one cup of hot chocolate, add 1/3 cup of the mix (more or less to taste) to a cup of boiling water.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in a 9 x
13 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, combine pineapple juice, ketchup, honey, vinegar, mustard and salt.
Pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Remove to serving platter and keep warm.
Strain pan juices into saucepan. Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to pan juices.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer. Serve over chops.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into florets.
Combine cauliflower, radishes, onions and chestnuts in a medium size mixing bowl.
Toss gently.
Stir together sour cream, mayonnaise and buttermilk dressing mix and pour over vegetables.
Stir well, spoon into serving bowl.
Cover and chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yellow chiffon cake
directions: Beat
egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, then add 1/2 cup sugar, beat in egg white mixture.
In another bowl take 1 cup sugar, flour and baking powder, then add egg yolks, water and oil;
beat
until
thick.
Fold in egg whites and 1 teaspoon vanilla or lemon flavoring.
Turn into ungreased 13 x 9 1/4-inch pan for 25 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 2 round pans (8 or 9 1/2-inch).
Drain peaches; reserve sauce.
Add enough water to reserved sauce to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute sauce mixture instead of water.
Bake and cool as directed.
Cut peaches into bite size pieces.
Mix yogurt and whipped topping.
Fold in peaches.
Fill layers with 1/2 peach mixture.
Spoon remaining mixture over top of cake.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: grandma's crunchy zucchini
directions: Split washed zucchini in half lengthwise.
Slice tomato 1/8-inch thick.
Cut each slice in half crosswise.
Put 3 half slices of tomato on each cut side of zucchini.
Combine butter, bread crumbs and salt; sprinkle 1 tablespoon of mixture on top of tomato and zucchini.
Place in shallow ovenware for microwave. Cook in microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender. Brown 5 to 7 minutes or until crumb topping is brown and crispy.

title: easy black forest torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle marshmallows in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package; pour over marshmallows.
Spoon pie filling over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of cake is clean. Cool.
Frost with whipped topping.

title: blender lemon pie
directions: Mix all in blender.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni as directed on package. Rinse with cold water and drain. Add mayonnaise and contents of cheese powder included in macaroni and cheese dinner. Toss well. Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: smoked salmon canapes
directions: Place the cream cheese and horseradish in a bowl and whip with an electric mixer or wire whisk until light and fluffy.
Stir in the minced herbs and season to taste with lemon juice and pepper. Spread on bread.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine corn and eggs. Add flour which has been sifted with remaining ingredients. Drop corn mixture from tablespoon into 1-inch of melted shortening. Brown until golden on both sides, turning once. Makes 12 fritters.

title: miss irene's mexican chicken
directions: Grease large casserole and cover bottom with chips that have been dipped in chicken stock.
Layer chicken, green pepper and onion.
Cover with cheese.
Mix soup, tomatoes, garlic and chili powder.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Top with more cheese and sprinkle paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough in 1/8-inch slices and arrange on a well-greased pizza pan.
Press edges together to seal and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread on baked cookie dough.
Arrange fruit in rings around the pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°. Freezes well.

title: easy and tasty cabbage dinner
directions: In large stock pot, place one layer of cabbage on bottom, then start layering onions, cabbage and sausage until all are used. Add wine and seasonings. Pour only about 2 to 3 inches of water in pot, enough to cover bottom and prevent sticking. Bring to a light boil, then reduce heat, cover and simmer until cabbage and onions are tender.

title: easy rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 2 qt. oven safe dish. Add rice and stir until rice is coated. Add consomme beef and soup. Cover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot pecan dip
directions: Toast pecans in butter in 350° oven until golden.
Whip remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add 1/2 cup toasted pecans. Stir well.
Spoon into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans on top.
Serve hot or cold. Serve with crackers.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion in butter in microwave.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese.
Put microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: mustard glazed fruit
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in sugar and mustard.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in fruits. Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until all fruits are heated through.
Serve warm with ham, turkey, pork or cold cuts.

title: oatmeal rolls
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, salt and boiling water. Stir until shortening is melted. Add oats and let stand until lukewarm. Mix yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water and add egg. Add this to the oatmeal mixture. Stir in 1 cup flour and beat hard. Add remaining flour and mix well. Cover with towel and refrigerate. Two hours before baking, roll dough into a large circle on

floured surface. Cut into pie shaped wedges (about 24). Brush with melted butter. Roll each wedge from wide edge to point. Place on baking pan. Brush with butter and let rise until doubled. Bake at 400° until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cool pie
directions: Mix Cool
Whip with yogurt and Sweet 'N Low.
Dry jello may be
added
for
extra color.
If you use low calorie Cool Whip, yogurt
and
jello
this
pie has very few calories per serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make two complete layers as follows: layer of tortillas, cheese, olives, onion and chiles.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread per directions on box using 2 eggs.
Add corn and set aside.
Brown hamburger meat
with onion and green chilies.
Salt and pepper meat mixture to taste.
Grease iron skillet or bread pan and pour in half of cornbread mixture.
Add meat mixture.
Add grated cheese.
Add rest of cornbread mixture, being careful to smooth out over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May require a little longer for golden brown top. Great with beans!

title: steaming vegetable beef stew
directions: Combine Soup Starter with beef, corn, potatoes, onion, celery, carrots and seasonings.
Add 8 cups of water.
Cook on medium for 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes and cook 15 minutes longer on low heat. It makes a delicious stew for those cold winter days.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Beat all together until well blended and thickened.
Place in covered container and chill for several hours.
Shake before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to other mixture.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325°
for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Brown the sausage and ground chuck separately and drain the fat.
Over low heat mix the meats, cheese, garlic salt and oregano until cheese melts.
Spread over the party rye rounds and freeze.
(May store in freezer bags until needed.)
Remove from freezer, place on a cookie sheet and broil for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: maple syrup
directions: Bring sugar, cream of tartar and water to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add maple flavoring.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Divide whipped topping among ten dessert glasses, using about 1/3 cup in each.
With the back of a spoon, make a depression in the center and spread topping up the sides of glasses.
Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Spoon into glasses. Chill.
Makes 10 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion with mixture of the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.

title: old-fashioned "dog bread"
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour boiling water in mixture to blend.
Mixture should be thick and almost dry consistency. Drop or pat out into patties and fry in canola oil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Please serve to humans; let the dog eat dog food!

title: grandma's rice
directions: Cook rice according to package, except replace water with chicken stock. Saut green onions in butter, then add onion mixture to rice right before serving. Mix well.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour and oleo.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Beat Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk. Spread on the cream cheese mixture.
Top with chopped nuts. Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: cherry oatmeal bar
directions: Cream shortening and sugar for 10 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients, add
to
creamed mixture.
Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Spread 2/3 of dough on greased 18 x 26-inch bun pan. Spread
tart
cherry
pie
filling
evenly
on entire surface. Cover with
remaining dough and pat down.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and waffles
directions: Combine soups, water and chicken.
Add Minute rice and stir to mix.
Bring quickly to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 7 minutes.
Top with onions.
Serve on waffles.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well, saving liquids for soups.
Add onion and green pepper to beans in a large bowl; mix well.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a 2 quart skillet, melt butter and add flour.
Whisk flour until completely blended.
Add heavy cream a little at a time, whisking constantly until blended.
Keep heat on high and continue to whisk until mixture thickens.
Add basil, thyme, salt and white pepper; whisk until blended.
Bring mixture to a medium boil and slowly add cream cheese a little at a time, whisking or stirring until blended.
If mixture is too thick, add a little milk until mixture is perfect for dipping.
Remove from heat; add crabmeat. Stir gently until completely blended.
Cover and allow to sit, off the stove, for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or with pastry shells.

title: tortilla soup
directions: You may add leftover vegetables to soup as desired.

title: pumpkin chiffon
directions: Cook berries in water and sugar.
Thicken with cornstarch. Cool; spoon berries in Cool Whip and serve or put on top of angel food cake.

title: fried won ton
directions: Saute meat in oil until brown and crumbly.
Add diced water chestnuts and onions.
Season with soy sauce, garlic powder, pepper and monosodium glutamate and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch dissolved in sake wine.
Add green onions and cook for 1 minute more.
Cool.
Wrap a teaspoon in won ton wrapper, folding diagonally and sealing edges by wetting with a dab of water or egg white.
Deep-fry in 360° oil until golden.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Sprinkle salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook and boil for 5 minutes.
Let mixture cool.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix well.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 1 month.

title: children's punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Gently stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over crushed ice.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and spread on pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix powdered sugar, condensed milk, chopped nuts, coconut and melted margarine; shape into desired shapes.
Dip into melted mixture of paraffin and chocolate chips.
Place on waxed paper until set.
This candy stores well in airtight container.

title: corn muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Grease muffin pan generously with shortening.
Set in a 400° oven.
Sift cornmeal, salt, soda and baking powder into mixing bowl.
Add sour milk and stir well.
Add the beaten egg and melted butter.
Heat muffin pan very hot.
Fill each cup and bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: In a
large
bowl,
combine
ground
beef,
pork, bread crumbs, onions, parsley, egg, salt, 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper and nutmeg.
Mix
well
and shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
In a large skillet, heat
1 1/2 teaspoons of the oil.
Add half the meatballs and
cook
over
medium
heat until browned, about 8 minutes; transfer
to
plate.
Repeat
with
remaining oil and meatballs. Add
broths to skillet and return other meatballs. Bring to
a boil,
lower
heat
and
simmer,
covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove meatballs
to a bowl.
Strain cooking liquid and reserve.
Return 1/2
cup
of
the liquid to the skillet. Whisk in flour until smooth.
Cook over medium heat 2 minutes. Slowly whisk
in remaining
liquid,
teaspoon pepper and thyme; simmer 5 minutes more.
Return meatballs to skillet and simmer in
gravy until
heated
through.
Serve
with whipped potatoes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box.
Use jellyroll pan; cool.
Drain pineapple; spread on cooled cake.
Mix pudding with milk and beat until thickens.
Add softened cream cheese and beat until thickens.
Spread on top of pineapple.
Add Cool Whip over pudding mix; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill; keep refrigerated.

title: dump cake
directions: Take pineapple and cherry filling and dump in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together.
In bowl, put cake mix and melted butter.
Work together until crumbly.
Put over fruit; sprinkle nuts on top and press down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hungry jack barbecue cups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown hamburger in large skillet; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Cook 5 minutes on low heat to blend flavors.

title: no-bake drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in saucepan.
Bring to full boil and boil for one minute.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Beat together.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: zucchini medley
directions: Saute in covered skillet for 15 minutes.
Mix 2 eggs and 1 tablespoon of grated cheese; spread over mixture.
Cook, covered, until eggs are firm.
Put skillet under broiler until brown.

title: squash-pepper casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and brown sugar in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir only to mix.
Fry in hot Crisco oil.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: lobster curry
directions: Sprinkle seafood and apple with curry; brown in melted butter. Put cooked rice in bottom of greased casserole.
Spoon lobster mixture over rice.
Combine mushroom soup with cream; pour over lobster.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix in order and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 100 bars.

title: creamed corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Put graham cracker crumbs in bowl.
Mix in 1 stick softened butter and pat into pan.

title: cream can dinner(simmering supper)
directions: (If you don't have cream can, you can use a Dutch oven or large covered pot or kettle on fire pit, outside with grill or indoors on stove.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown meat
and onion.
Place in the bottom of a casserole. Add
green
beans (drained).
Add soup and place potato tots on top
to
cover casserole.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are brown.

title: all-in-one hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and spread in the bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with thawed mixed vegetables.
Heat together soup and Cheez Whiz until smooth.
Pour over meat/vegetables.
Top with the Tater Tots in a solid single layer.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and Tater Tots are browned.

title: yogurt banana sips
directions: Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed until smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: dutch oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake covered in a 275° oven for 5 hours.
Not necessary to brown meat.
Serves 6.
I always add celery to mine.

title: herbed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into pieces 1/4-inch thick and 2 1/2-inches long. Heat oil in large skillet.
Add zucchini (it shouldn't be layered more than 1/2-inch thick so it will steam and soften without browning).
Saute 4 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Add chives, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
The zucchini should be soft and a bit transparent, not soggy.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a mixer.
Mix until combined. Pour into the pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 pie.

title: cream cheese coffee pecan cake
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Spread 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of topping over batter.
Repeat with rest of batter and topping.

title: cherry-orange fizz
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large pitcher.
Chill.
Add orange cubes and ginger ale before serving.
Float cherries and orange slices on top.
Add fresh mint to each glass as a garnish.

title: southern skillet chicken creole
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet; brown chicken and remove from skillet.
In remaining shortening, saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and rice is cooked.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mock lobster salad
directions: Broil haddock, cool and then flake.
Add celery, onion, catsup and mayonnaise.
Make a day ahead.
Serve with crackers.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple. Put all ingredients together and whip with mixer until light and fluffy.

title: pecan pie *
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it does not stick to knife.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up chicken and layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour melted oleo over chicken.
Mix flour and milk over chicken.
Mix soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and egg.
Fold in 8 ounce Cool Whip.
Pour over pretzel mix and cool.
Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries.
Cool and pour over top.
Refrigerate.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Add apples, celery and raisins; toss.
Cover; chill.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes eight 1/2-cup servings.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: a great salad
directions: Soak
broccoli
and
cauliflower in salt water for three hours.
Rinse and chop vegetables; add dressing.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans and drain.
Fry bacon and remove from pan when crisp.
Using bacon drippings, add flour and then milk to make a sauce.
Add Italian dressing mix and lima beans.
Mix well.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with crumbled bacon and the cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: banana praline sundae
directions: In 10-inch skillet over low heat, melt together sugar and butter, stirring frequently.
Add raisins and bananas; cook 5 minutes or until fruit is heated thoroughly, gently turning fruit. Serve over ice cream; top with nuts.

title: onion soup
directions: Slice onions and saute until light brown.
Add flour, mustard and seasonings carefully.
Add water or broth and simmer for at least 3 hours or more.

title: company peach pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, salt and peaches.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Add meringue and brown.

title: breezy puff bowl
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Heat water and butter to rolling boil in 2 quart saucepan.
Add Bisquick mix all at once.
Stir vigorously over medium heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, with a spoon.
Continue beating until smooth. Spread in pie plate (do not spread up side).
Bake until center is dry, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Fill with fruit and/or ice cream.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in
boiling
water; add sherbet, stirring until
melted.
Chill
until consistency of unbeaten egg white. Fold
in
remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly oiled 6-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: hello dolly
directions: Melt one stick oleo. Add 1 1/2 cups graham crackers, crushed. Put into oblong pan and press.

title: van camp's pork and beans pitas
directions: Combine first two ingredients in 1 1/2-quart microwavable casserole.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until heated through.
If desired, line each pita half with lettuce leaf and tomato slices.
Spoon heaping 1/2 cup bean mixture into each pita half; sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: golden glow meat loaf surprise
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and press half into bottom of baking pan.
Make an indentation in the shape of a large well.
Fill with the macaroni dinner.
Cover with remaining meat mixture, pressing well around edges to seal macaroni in the center of the meat loaf.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: oven baked sliced potatoes
directions: If you want to leave the skins on the potatoes, you may. Otherwise, peel each potato and drop it into a bowl of cold water to keep it from browning.
Slice each potato into 1/4 inch slices and return slices to the cold water.
Line a 15 x 10 inch pan with foil.
Distribute the butter, garlic, thyme and onion over the foil and heat in a 450° oven just until the butter is melted. Stir well.
Drain the potato slices and dry on paper towels. Arrange the slices in the butter mixture, turning to coat both sides of the slices; overlap as/if necessary.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°.
Remove from oven and drizzle with lemon juice and sprinkle with parmesan.
Return to the oven and continue baking 10-15 minutes, or until golden.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage 6 to 8 minutes; break up and drain fat.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine biscuit mix, cheese and cooked sausage with a fork.
In a small bowl, beat remaining ingredients with another fork.
Add sausage mixture; blend well. Shape into balls using 1 tablespoon.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each ball slightly.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls and bake about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Easier to work with if cheese is at room temperature.
(Can be mixed, ready to bake, frozen, then bake as you need them.)

title: spicy apple compote
directions: In large saucepan, dissolve concentrate in water.
Add sugar, lemon, cinnamon stick and cloves.
Bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar, adding 5 or 6 apple halves once, 6 to 8 minutes, or until almost tender.
Discard lemon, cinnamon and cloves. Chill and serve or store, covered, in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: fresh peach pudding
directions: Beat well the eggs, sugar and butter.
Add Cool Whip and peaches.
Layer vanilla wafers, then the pudding.
Makes 2 to 3 layers.
Refrigerate.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine chocolate chips and butter; stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add milk; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine 1 level cup of flour, finely chopped nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoon of dough completely around each kiss.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and appear shiney but become firm as they cool. Remove and cool.
In saucepan, mix baking bar and shortening.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Drizzle over cookies. Makes 5 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Melt margarine; blend in flour.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick.
Add salt, pepper, onion and cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Mix sauce with macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: soup
directions: Cook it with hot water on the stove.
Then get it the counter and eat it.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: May use drained Bavarian sauerkraut.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: potato beef casserole
directions: In greased baking dish, layer potatoes, onion, carrots and beef.
Combine soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over top of casserole.
Cover and bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook an additional 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Mix well. Form ball. Add more powdered sugar if desired for thicker consistency. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Serve with graham crackers.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Separate eggs and reserve egg whites in separate bowl.
Cream shortening, 1 cup sugar, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Whip egg whites until stiff and fold in. Roll blueberries in flour and fold in.
Grease and flour pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Pour batter in pan and sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown and toothpick clean.

title: neon honey mustard chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Stir in honey, mustard, salt and curry powder.
Arrange chicken in dish in a single layer and cover with honey mixture.
Cover.
Bake for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake another 30 minutes.
Great served with rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl and mix well.
Butter both sides of all bread slices.
Dip each slice in egg mixture. Place 1 layer of bread in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup cheese, all of the ham, the remaining bread slices and the remaining cheese.
Pour remaining egg mixture over the cheese. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: my favorite pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco; beat until creamy.
Add flavoring and milk alternately with flour.
Last, add eggs, one at a time.
Use tube cake pan and start in a cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: beans and franks
directions: Slice hot dogs up and mix with all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: upside down dinner casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with bacon slices.
Press the ground beef on top of bacon followed with sliced onion, carrots and sliced raw potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour on one can of soup.
Cover and bake until vegetables are tender at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nut tarts
directions: Blend room temperature cream cheese, butter, and flour; chill one hour.
Divide into 24 equal parts.
Shape each part into a small ball.
Press onto bottom and 1/2-inch up the side of small buttered (2-inch) muffin cups; chill.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip. Add fresh cut up berries. Pour into pie shell. Freeze for several hours. Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: old fashion mayonnaise
directions: Beat eggs until foamy in medium size pan.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in flour until mixture is smooth.
Add milk and stir; add vinegar and mix well.
Put on stove and add boiling water and stir constantly until mixture is boiling good.
Remove from stove and stir in oleo until melted.
Pour into bowl and cover with waxed paper or plastic wrap to keep crust from forming. Cool.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix well the sugar, salt, flour and cocoa. Beat in eggs and melted margarine. Add milk. Add pecans, coconut and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Heat together rice (uncooked), milk, mushrooms with liquid and soups.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Add sugar to sliced, fresh strawberries.
In saucepan, add strawberries and gelatin.
Dissolve over medium heat.
Cool.

title: stir - fajitas(microwave)
directions: Cut chicken into 1/4-inch slices; add dressing.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain chicken; keep dressing. Microwave chicken in a 2-quart bowl on High 4 to 5 minutes; cook until tender.
Drain chicken.
Combine pepper, onion and 2 tablespoons dressing.
Put back into the bowl (2-quart), microwave 4 to 5 minutes until tender.
Add chicken and tomatoes; mix lightly.
Microwave 2 minutes or until hot.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs.
Mix well. Sift flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda and salt together and add to mixture.
Add nuts, dates and apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inches) and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken and dumplings(simple)
directions: Mix well and put out on your floured cloth.
Knead gently, adding a little flour as needed so you can roll it out like pie crust.
Let it lay a while to dry, 10 to 15 minutes.
I use my pizza cutter to cut in strips.
I bring the pot of chicken broth to a boil before I drop the strips in one by one; after all are in, turn heat down.
Stir and cook slowly for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: holiday honey nog
directions: In large bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Add yolks and honey; mix well. Stir in milk, rum extract, vanilla and cinnamon. Chill. Just before serving, fold in whipped cream; pour into large pitcher or punch bowl. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg. Makes 16 (4 oz.) servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat oil in skillet and cook onion until browned.
Place refried beans, salt, garlic powder and spices in skillet and heat through.
Pour about half of the Chili Sauce in ungreased 3-quart baking dish.
Warm tortillas (directions on package).
Place 1/3 cup bean mixture on tortilla and roll up.
Place flap side down in sauce in baking dish.
Repeat until all tortillas are used.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Bake, uncovered in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli pecan casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Add eggs and onion. Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Drizzle top with melted butter.

title: early morning pancakes
directions: Mash the potatoes until smooth with the remaining ingredients. Should be moist to form into patties.
Place on a well-oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 40 minutes, turning once.
Pancakes should form a brown crust.
Serve with fresh parsley and tomatoes. A complement to tofu.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice with lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Soak gelatin in cold water and add to heated mixture.
Pour into 9 inch by 12 inch casserole dish and put in refrigerator.
When it begins to congeal, add cheese, pimento, and cool whip.
Stir and put back in refrigerator.
Let chill overnight.
Makes 15 generous servings.

title: cabbage casserole #2
directions: In buttered casserole dish, layer thin sliced potatoes, layer of sliced onions, layer of shredded cabbage, layer of corned beef. Top with 1 can golden mushroom soup.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Bake according to number of servings.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cook bacon then crumble into pieces and set aside.

title: curried-broccoli chicken
directions: Boil chicken 20 minutes or microwave.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Bone chicken.
Cut into 4 to 6 large pieces.
Put broccoli in buttered casserole.
Add chicken.
Combine rest of ingredients except crumbs. Pour over chicken.
Top with crumbs. Bake uncovered at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in butter.
Add eggs, cheese, salt, cornbread mix and garlic powder to broccoli and onion.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turtlettes
directions: In saucepan, heat and melt butter and evaporated milk.
In another pan, cook to firm ball stage (244°), stirring often the sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Slowly stir in hot milk mixture so that sugar mixture does not stop boiling.
Stirring constantly, cook mixture until candy reaches firm ball stage again.
Remove pan from heat; stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.

title: black raspberry pie
directions: Boil water; mix next 3 ingredients and stir into boiling water until thick.
Stir in jello.
Remove from heat.
Stir in raspberries and add flavorings.
Pour into your favorite unbaked pie shell and place on lowest rack in oven at 375° for 15 minutes, then turn oven to 350° and bake until golden brown.
Makes one 9-inch double crust pie.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Brown ribs in 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 of sauce over ribs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn.
Add rest of sauce and bake another 40 minutes.

title: almond candy cookies
directions: Mix evaporated milk and 2 squares of chocolate in saucepan, cook 5-6 minutes until chocolate is melted and mixture is thick and smooth.
Mix together coconut, vanilla and salt, blend very well.
Pour chocolate mixture over coconut mixture and blend well. Drop by teaspoonful on a cookie sheet covered with parchment paper.
Top each cookie with a whole almond.
Bake at 350 F for 10-12 minutes.
Check after 8 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cookies should be soft but firm.
Cool completely.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of 3 (9-inch) cake pans with waxed paper.
Sift together flour and soda.
Cream Crisco thoroughly, adding sugar gradually, until light and fluffy.
Add 2 tablespoons milk and then eggs.
Add dry ingredients and remaining milk alternately, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Fold mashed bananas into batter.
Pour into cake pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foaming.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and salt until most of the sugar has dissolved.
Add milk and cream.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 4-quart ice cream freezer can.

title: party dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into pieces.
Mix mustard and jelly.
Put in crock-pot and simmer on high for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix everything together except nuts.
Form into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Let set approximately 2 days.

title: german potato salad
directions: You will need a large jar with lid.
Add all the ingredients, crushing the garlic with a press.
Before serving, add Parmesan cheese.
Serve over crisped romaine lettuce.
No tomatoes necessary!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add 1 can tomato soup.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix can of chicken soup with noodles.
Layer hamburger mixture, then cheese, then noodles and sliced cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: twisty pretzels
directions: Mix yeast, flours, sugar and salt in bowl.
Add water and mix until ball can be formed.
Sprinkle table with about 1 tablespoon flour and rub some on hands.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 4 to 5 minutes.
Punch and squeeze until dough feels like a rubber ball.
Break off walnut-sized pieces.
Roll each into rods, about 8-inches long.
Shape into pretzels.
Brush with beaten egg. Sprinkle salt on.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Bake pretzels at 450° for about 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Use 3 1/2-quart crock-pot and cook 6 hours on low.

title: oil pie crust(makes 1 large or 2 small crusts.)
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Make well in center.
Next blend oil and milk well.
Pour in well.
Mix until it makes a ball.
Roll out between 2 sheets of waxed paper.

title: queenie's favorite dog biscuits
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and roll out on a floured board or table top.
Cut with bone shaped cookie cutter and bake on cookie sheet lightly sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Let set until cool on wire rack.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse and drain peas.
Combine in large pot with water, ham, onion, carrots, celery, parsley, bay leaf and salt.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer partially covered for 3 hours, skimming often.
Remove and discard bay leaf and ham bone (shred meat and set aside).
Puree soup in blender or processor. Add ham, pepper and pepper sauce.
If soup is too thin, return to heat and simmer until desired consistency is reached.
Makes 2 quarts.
Has about 250 calories per cup.

title: chocolate cinnamon brownies
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Put margarine, cocoa and 1 cup water into saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix and pour into greased sheet pan.
(Pan should be large, such as a broiler pan.)
Batter should be about 1/2-inch thick in pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: mom's steak fries
directions: Wash
potatoes and dry.
Do not peel.
Slice in strips. Roll in melted margarine.
Spray baking pan or dish with Pam. Layer potatoes, put skin side down; salt and pepper.
Sprinkle paprika on
top
of
potatoes.
(Can
also
sprinkle Parmesan cheese
on potatoes,
if desired.) Bake at 350° to 375° until tender and golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, syrup, nuts, salt, vanilla and chopped up butter or margarine.
Put into unbaked pie shell and bake about 50 minutes in oven at 325°.
The pecans will float and form crust on top if baked slowly.

title: chocolate junk
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and rice according to package directions. Place margarine in skillet, along with onion and celery, and saute.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz to saute mixture, then add broccoli and rice and fold into mixture.
Place mixture in casserole; cover with a layer of grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: twenty-four hour breakfast casserole
directions: Place 8 slices	of bread on bottom of greased casserole dish. Alternate cheese,
then
meat.
Add
more
slices of bread, cheese and	meat.
Beat eggs then add milk, mustard and salt. Pour
over	bread.	Cover
with
foil
and	refrigerate overnight. Top with cornflake crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: applesauce cookies(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cream oleo, brown sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture and beat well.
Fold in raisins and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until firm.
Makes 36 cookies.
Two cookies equal 1 bread and 1 fruit.

title: frozen bread dough caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough, but do not allow it to rise.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tear one loaf of dough into pieces and scatter in pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan; add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour half of mixture over bread in pan.
Tear other loaf of dough into pieces and place in pan.
Pour remaining cooked mixture over dough.
Allow to rise (2 to 3 hours).
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool 5 minutes and turn out onto wax paper.

title: impossible shrimp pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a deep 10-inch pie plate. Mix shrimp, cheeses and onion in the pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth 15 seconds on high speed in a blender or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour over shrimp mixture. Bake until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to set.
Cut into 6 or 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature, combine and mix well.
Add paprika and Bisquick; mix well.
Roll into small balls and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Do not over brown.

title: big toll house cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat margarine, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a 14 or 15-inch round pizza pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool; cut in wedges.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in margarine; add to squash. Stir in crumbled cornbread and 2 cups milk.
Add can of soup. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Line 10-inch pie plate or 10 x 15-inch dish with crescent rolls.
Spread with 2 tablespoons mustard.
Melt butter; add squash, onions and spices.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Mix in separate bowl 2 eggs (beaten) and 8 ounces cheese.
Add to veggies.
Pour in dish.
Bake for 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Set 10 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat the eggs well and mix with the cottage cheese.
Add broccoli, thawed and cooked.
Add soft butter, Cheddar cheese (diced), flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all well and put in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken dish
directions: Cook chicken until tender; save broth.
Best to strain chicken broth.
Add onion, celery, crackers, cheese and eggs to chicken broth.
Pick chicken off bone and add 2 cans chicken soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake until brown or 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge 1
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in a sauce pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until it comes to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, still stirring.
Take off heat and add marshmallow cream, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Stir until well mixed.
Add nuts and mix again. Pour into a greased 9x12 inch pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Then drain.
In a casserole dish combine butter and brown sugar.
Add carrots.
Stir to coat and glaze.	Bake in a preheated oven 350° 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield 8 servings.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Add spices.
Mix well.
Add yams and flour (may have to add a little more flour).
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Add the pecans and cherries.
Put mixture into the 2 pie crusts.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and shape into small balls.
Chill.
Makes 18 to 20 balls.

title: brownie drops
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in top of a double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cool until chocolate melts, stirring occasionally. Cool and set aside.

title: perfect pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and mix remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: cathedral stained glass salad
directions: Fix the first 3 boxes of colored Jell-O and let them jell.
Cut into small irregular pieces (keeping each color separate).
Fix the box of lemon Jell-O, using only 1/2 the specified amount of water. After dissolving the Jell-O, add ice cubes to make up the difference in the 1/2 water you omitted.
Stir until the mixture begins to thicken.
Whip the cream and after removing any remaining ice cubes that are in the lemon Jell-O, add the lemon Jell-O and the whipped cream together.
Then add the cubed red/green/orange Jell-O to this mixture and stir carefully, so as not to break the pieces or make them run together.

title: cucumbers gourmet
directions: Slice cucumbers in thin slices and onions in rings.
Place in a bowl; salt well.
Let stand in refrigerator 1 hour.
Rinse well and drain thoroughly.
In the bowl, mix cucumbers, onion, sugar and vinegar.
Let stand overnight.
Refrigerate.

title: skippy's fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, water, raisins, dates, candied fruit, candied cherries, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Boil together.
Let cool.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Spoon into 3 large bread pans or 5 small bread pans.
Bake in a 300° to 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Wrap in cloth soaked in dry white wine, then in Saran Wrap, and then in aluminum foil. Store in a cool place.

title: seven seas chicken
directions: Mix and soak chicken several hours.
Grill 6 minutes on each side.

title: ice cream pudding dessert
directions: Mix together the cracker crumbs and melted butter or oleo; save 1/2 cup for top.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the pudding with the milk.
Add more coconut.
Soften the ice cream; mix in pudding mixture.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Cut into small pieces.
Save broth. Into a large (at least 10 to 12-quart) kettle, put beef broth and add all ingredients except beef.
Add water to make consistency you like (thick or thin soup).
Add beef; simmer for at least 1 hour, longer is better.
Add salt and ground black pepper to taste.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Put in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour Pizza Quick sauce over beef.
Top with cheese.
Mix Bisquick mix with milk and eggs and pour over top. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Kids love this one!

title: cobbler for peach, blueberry or blackberry
directions: Put fruit in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cream the butter and sugar with a fork.
Blend in the flour with the fork to form little clumps.
Spread over fruit and bake until browned and bubbly.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese together until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix together.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple and nuts. Pour into 8 inch square dish and freeze.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Drain the cans of fruit extra good.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball and put chopped pecans on outside.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle top with 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: citrus melon mingle
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Beat margarine and 1/2 cup powdered sugar with electric mixer until light and fluffy, scraping down side of bowl once. Gradually add 1 cup flour, vanilla and salt.
Beat at low speed until well blended, scraping down side of bowl once.
Stir in remaining flour and pecans with spoon.
Form dough into ball; wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat, onion and peppers.
Mix corn bread per directions. Stir in corn and soup; add to hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly in 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° about 20 minutes or until mixture is heated and cheese is melted.

title: teriyaki venison steaks
directions: 1. Combine the soy, oil, molasses, ginger, mustard, and garlic in a flat dish. Mix well.
2. Cut steak into strips and add them to the marinade in
the dish and let soak for at least 15 minutes but
perferably 1 hour. Turn steak so both sides get exposed
to the marinade.
3. Place steaks on grill and cook until done (they can
burn easily so keep a close eye).

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all these ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: joy's salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. "BOURSIN CHEESE"

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni.
Layer macaroni in casserole dish.
Put dabs of butter on top of macaroni, then layer cheese over butter and macaroni.
Repeat macaroni, butter and cheese.
Mix in a small bowl the milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Pour this over the last layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick cherry pie
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and mix pineapple and cherry pie filling in pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over that.
Cut butter over cake mix.
Cook for 20 minutes, then add chopped nuts.
Cook for 20 more minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip for topping or serve plain.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Combine warm cooked noodles with Parmesan cheese; stir until coated.
Chill.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to noodles.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 3 parts.
Cook regular way.
While cooking the spaghetti, chop pepper, cucumber, tomatoes and onion into bowl.
Add olives, Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.
After draining spaghetti, add to mixture; mix well.
Marinate overnight.

title: susan musman's avocado pie
directions: Pit and peel the avocado and put it into the blender with the juice of 1 lemon.
Add the condensed milk.
Whip until smooth and of even consistency.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Garnish with pecans.

title: creamy pecans
directions: Cook sugars and sour cream over low heat, stirring, until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Stir and spoon onto wax paper.

title: beef rice balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mushroom soup and water.
Form meatballs the size of a walnut and arrange in baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and water; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour three 9-inch round cake pans. Cream butter and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well between each. Stir together salt, baking powder and flour. Set aside. Add vanilla to milk. Set aside. Add flour mixture to butter, sugar and eggs, alternating with milk. Mix well. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans to complete cooling.

title: easy bread or rolls
directions: Mix first five ingredients in bowl.
Add the rest and mix well.
Add 2 or 3 more cups flour to make stiff dough; but stirrable dough.
Set timer for 10 minutes, stir dough.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk or buttermilk and beat.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add 1/2 cup of the dry ingredients to egg mixture and beat well.
Mash bananas and beat into dry ingredients.
Mix well and add chopped walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center top is firm to finger test.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Blend all the ingredients together and chill.
Serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: special "bones"
directions: In small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large bowl, combine broth, powdered milk, margarine, honey, egg and salt.
Add yeast and water and mix well.
Stir in all-purpose flour, wheat germ, cornmeal and cracked wheat; mix well.
Add whole wheat flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well after each.
Knead in final amounts and continue kneading 4 to 5 minutes until not sticky. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick and cut into shapes.
Place on greased sheet and let set 20 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Turn off heat and leave in oven for several hours or overnight.

title: almond cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust and chill.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add 2/3 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat all together until smooth.
Stir in almond extract and pour into crust.
Bake for 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: get together punch
directions: Day before, pour 1 can of punch in 1 1/2 qt. ring mold; freeze.
Mix remaining punch, pineapple juice, lemonade, and club soda in punch bowl.
Just before serving, unmold frozen punch and place in punch bowl.
Place lemon slices around outside of frozen punch mold.
Fill center of mold with mint or white orchids.

title: sassy sue's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and baste poultry or pork.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put in 2 greased bread pans (4 x 8 1/2-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rabbit mediterranean
directions: Place rabbit pieces in bag with flour, salt and pepper.
Saute onion in oil until soft.
Push aside, add rabbit and brown on all sides.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, bay leaves and red wine. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add olives and continue simmering until meat is tender.
If sauce does not thicken, mix a little flour and water; stir in.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass baking dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwave bowl on High 2 minutes, or until margarine is melted.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 fudgy brownies.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and salt.
Mix again.
Add dissolved yeast and cooled milk; blend well.
Add flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each cup.
Put on floured board and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl and turn dough on each side until greased.
Let rise, covered, in refrigerator overnight.

title: heart-smart stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean mushrooms.
Remove and finely chop stems.
Heat oil over medium heat.
Saute chopped mushroom stems, onion, garlic and walnuts until onion is tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in Shredded Wheat, Parmesan cheese, herb and spice seasoning and pepper.
Stuff mushroom caps, packing mixture firmly.
Arrange mushrooms in a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle tops lightly with paprika.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: light strawberry cheesecake
directions: Coat bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray. Distribute cookie crumbs evenly across pan bottom.
Set aside. Process cottage cheese and cream cheese until smooth.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and whole eggs.
Pour into large bowl and set aside.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually blend in remaining sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Gently stir 1/4 egg white mixture into cheese mixture.
Gently fold in remaining egg white mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool. Chill 8 hours.
Glaze with following mixture.

title: autumn soup
directions: Mix meat, onion and celery in 5-quart casserole.
Microwave at High until meat loses its pink color, about 5 to 7 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
Add hot water, potatoes, carrots, salt, basil, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover and microwave at High until potatoes are tender, 18 to 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and microwave at High until tomatoes are tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stompolst
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender.
